title: hot mulled cider
directions: Simmer all over low heat 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or warm. Makes 2 quarts.

title: snappy wieners
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Score wieners diagonally.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Arrange wieners in sauce, turning to coat well.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: chocolate amaretto pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
With Crisco shortening, grease Bundt pan. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, extracts and cocoa; beat until smooth.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Gently blend in egg whites.
Add Amaretto.
Mix well until creamy.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour or until done.
Let cake stand in pan 20 to 30 minutes and then invert onto wire rack.
Top cooled cake with sifted powdered sugar.
Add cherries on top for final holiday touch.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, water, and vanilla, in a mixing bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour and oatmeal.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Season to taste with black pepper.
Refrigerate.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine sugar, Accent, salt, pepper, vinegar and oil together. Mix and chill.
Combine cabbage, onions and noodles.
Mix together.
Toast almonds and sesame seed in 350° oven for 5 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle on top of cabbage mixture.
Toss salad with dressing right before serving.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Put all ingredients except eggs in blender or food processor (hand mixer). Blend until smooth. Add eggs and blend for only a second or two.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes until filling is set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together in a large bowl.
Stir in the walnuts. Make a well in the center of these ingredients and add the oil, eggs and pumpkin puree.
Stir until the ingredients are well blended, then fold in the raisins and rum.
Spread the batter into prepared pans and bake for 1 hour.
Allow to cool in the pans before removing and cutting.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: cranberry refrigerator cake
directions: Mix together cranberries, banana and sugar.
Set aside. Place 1/2 of the crushed wafers in bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cream together butter and confectioners sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Spread
over the crumbs.
Top with a layer of the cranberry-banana
mixture
adding
the nuts and spreading whipped cream over it.
Cover with remaining wafers and chill overnight.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix 1/2 butter, soup, cheese, sour cream, onions, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Mix remaining 1/2 butter with crumbled corn flakes.
Top casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad no. 1
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and cold water; boil until berries are tender.
Remove from heat and add jello which has been dissolved in boiling water.
When berries and jello mixture has cooled, add celery, apples and nuts.
Mix and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange pecan halves on top to decorate. Refrigerate several hours.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, broth and soup together.
In oblong or square pan, layer soup, tortillas, soup, tortillas and soup.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in medium size bowl.
Combine last 3 ingredients in separate bowl.
Mix well, pour over salad, blend and refrigerate.

title: smoked shrimp
directions: Melt margarine and pour into pan.
Place shrimp in margarine. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Place on smoker for 1 hour.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place chops in an
ovenproof
pan.
Place a lemon slice on each
chop,
then
a spoon of sugar on each slice of lemon, then a tablespoon of catsup on top of the sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Discard all hard corn kernels.
Use a large pan (such as turkey roasting pan) to mix in.
Combine syrup, sugar, water, vinegar and salt; cook slowly, stirring constantly to 270° or to hard ball stage (test by dropping a spoonful in cold water).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and oil, stirring only enough to mix.
Pour over popped corn, stirring constantly until all corn is coated.
Slip Baggies on both hands; grease lightly.
Work quickly; shape lightly into balls.
Put popcorn balls on wax paper to cool, then wrap each in its own Baggie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand except pecans.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans until covered.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Add drained beans and soup; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes while hot; add milk and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon in mounds over casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple spread
directions: Blend cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in ginger and pineapple.
Chill.
Let set at room temperature 1/2 hour before serving.
Yields 3 cups.
(Best if made a day or two ahead of time.)
Serve with crackers or as a filling for small sandwiches.

title: mekluba
directions: Saute onions in 1 1/2 teaspoons of oil until transparent. Remove onions and set aside.
Place meat or poultry in reserved oil.
Saute until lightly brown, then cover with water.
Bring to a boil and skim off foam.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add onions.
Reserve the stock.

title: reuben en croute
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Stir in sauerkraut, 1/4 cup mustard and caraway seed.
Melt remaining butter.
Stack phyllo dough sheets, brushing butter in between each layer.
Top with layers of corned beef, cheese and sauerkraut mixture to within 1 inch of edges. Roll up from long edge, jelly-roll fashion, tucking in ends and brushing seams with butter.
Place roll seam side down on greased baking sheet.
Cut slits on top of roll in 12 even sections about 1/2-inch deep.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: "popeye for breakfast"
directions: Split and toast an English muffin.
Top with a poached egg on each half.
Saute a small package of frozen spinach (well drained) with garlic in a little olive oil.
Put this on top of the poached eggs.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave long enough to melt the cheese.
Great breakfast to start your day!!

title: carbonara
directions: Stir-fry sausage and ham until lightly brown.
Remove from wok.
Have all ingredients ready and measured. Add hot spaghetti to meat with butter and parsley.
Mix well.
At once, pour in eggs and continue to blend quickly, lifting and mixing the pasta to coat well.
Sprinkle in the 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and a dash of pepper.
Mix again.
Serve and top with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken 5 minutes or until done and juices evaporate, stirring often. Add soup and salsa. Heat through. Place tortillas on 2 baking sheets. Top half of each tortilla with about 1/2 cup soup mixture. Spread to within 1/2-inch of edge. Moisten edges of tortillas with water. Fold over and seal. Bake 5 minutes or until hot.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Mix in both milks gradually. Blend in salt and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold in egg whites and rum flavoring.
Pour into chilled punch bowl.
Garnish with sprinkling of nutmeg and whipped cream, if desired.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 box yellow cake mix over pumpkin. Melt 1 3/4 sticks margarine; pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: herb casserole bread(1 loaf)
directions: In a
large bowl, combine 2 cups of flour, sugar, salt, basil, oregano,
garlic
powder
and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Margarine need not melt. Add
to
dry ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/2 cup of flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Stir
in
enough
remaining
flour	to
make stiff batter.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend well.
Add 5 pounds cleaned shrimp; mix well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve with crackers or may be served as a shrimp salad on lettuce.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Mix together with a mixer until smooth.

title: caramel cakewiches
directions: Fold banana into Cool Whip.
Chill.
Combine caramels with milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until caramels are melted; stir in bitters.
To serve, top cake slices with banana mixture, then with warm caramel sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in casserole dish.
Pour remaining ingredients over them.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix as directed on pudding package.
Pour into popsicle molds. Freeze.
Makes 12.

title: borscht
directions: Put bay leaf and parsley in cheese cloth bag.
In a 6 to 8-quart pot, melt butter.
Add onions and saute until soft.
Stir in the beets.
Add red wine vinegar, sugar, tomatoes and juice, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and 2 to 3 cups beef stock.
Cover and simmer undisturbed for 45 to 50 minutes.
Add remaining stock, cabbage and bring to boil.
Add meats, bay leaf and parsley; simmer partially covered for 30 minutes.
You can cut the cooking time by using canned beets, drained of half of their stock, then cut the cooking time by 20 minutes.
Serve with real coarse bread and butter.

title: eclair cake - 2
directions: Mix pudding as directed minus 1 cup milk.
Add Cool Whip. Layer graham crackers, pudding mixture and another layer of graham crackers.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place spareribs in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Chop onion; brown in fat.
Add remaining ingredients; cook slowly 20 minutes.
Pour over spareribs.
Continue baking about 1 hour.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel pears and cut up.
Grind pears with large cutter.
Cook juice and pears together; add sugar.
Cook until thick (1 hour approximately), stirring frequently.
Add pineapple; cook 20 minutes or longer.
Put into hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast before measuring anything, but yeast is last ingredient to go in.
Stir with wooden spoon or mix with hands. Knead dough until it feels good (the more you knead, the better it is).
Let rise for 2 to 3 hours in covered bowl.

title: creamy cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese, nuts and garlic in mixing bowl; stir to blend. Divide into 3 parts and shape into 3 balls.
Coat 1 ball with chili powder, one with parsley and one with nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until crumbly; spread in flat pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, stirring several times. Remove from oven; press firmly into desired pan.
Chill.
Fill with either chocolate or butter pecan ice cream.
Reserve some crumbs for topping.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar well.
Add flour and stir in milk and flavoring.
Pour into 2 9-inch frozen pie shells and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, soup, 1/4 cup margarine, onion, cheese, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cornflakes crumbs; drizzle with 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes.
May omit topping if preferred.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute gently onion in butter.
Add next three ingredients. Stir in hot milk.
Simmer slowly for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put in blender for 1 minute.
Before serving, sprinkle with grated cheese and pop under the broiler to brown. Yields 6 servings.
Very tasty.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients to make a waffle-like batter.
Heat 2-inches of vegetable shortening in a 9-inch iron skillet to 350°.
It must be very hot.
Pour the batter through a funnel into the skillet, going round and round in a coil-like pattern until the pan is covered with batter ropes.
Fry brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve with molasses.

title: seafood stew
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain grease from bacon to be added to stew.
For those who want to cut down on fat, use only 1/2 pound of bacon. (Note:
You can nibble on cooked bacon while you cook.)

title: easy hamburger goulash
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet with onion and garlic.
Pour off grease.
Add spaghetti and beans; let simmer until good and hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine with the cheese.
Crush crackers in a plastic bag.
Put 1/2 of the cracker crumbs in butter and cheese mixture.
Pour over broccoli.
Put the remainder of the cracker crumbs in the remaining butter (melted) and sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Brown chicken well in hot butter in large skillet.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup. Combine reserved syrup, brown sugar and vinegar in small bowl; pour over chicken.

Turn chicken, skin side down if using frying pieces. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until fork tender, about 20 minutes. Move chicken to side of skillet. Add the pineapple, water and salt. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.* Flour may be seasoned with 1/4 teaspoon each pepper and ground nutmeg, or 1/2 teaspoon paprika and 1/4 teaspoon ground ginger.

title: dietetic cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Defrost 2 regular (9-inch) pie shells. Combine margarine, sugar and flour.
Beat with mixer until blended.
Add to this the eggs, vanilla flavoring and buttermilk. Continue beating with mixer until well blended.
Pour equal amounts into pie shells.
Sprinkle cinnamon/sugar mixture over the top of pies.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: earline's shrimp salad
directions: Drain shrimp.
Mix all ingredients and serve.
The more shrimp the better.

title: granola snack bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together butter, sugar and corn syrup until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add oats and chocolate chips; mix well.
Press into pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk and roll out.
Cut into biscuits.
Do not let rise. Bake at 500° or 475°.

title: crispy enchilada casserole
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups grated cheese, enchilada sauce, chili, tomato paste, water, onion and all but 1 cup corn chips.
Pour into lightly greased oblong baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spread sour cream over top, sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Make a circle of remaining corn chips around edge.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chilies rellenos bake
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 of chilies on bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Arrange remaining chilies on top. Combine eggs, milk, flour, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt until smooth. Pour over chilies.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned and knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: strata with ham
directions: Spread butter on both sides of bread, then cut into cubes. Combine bread, ham, cheeses, salt and pepper; stir well.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in milk.
Add eggs and milk to other mixture; stir well.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: garden spiral salad
directions: Cook rotini; drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix all ingredients except dressing.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large pot bring water to a boil.
Add macaroni, stirring occasionally and cook until done.
Rinse and drain.
Add and mix together well seasonings, butter, cheese and milk.
Pour into large baking pan and top with cheese and butter chunks.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour until bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 10 servings.

title: better than school cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Let cool.
Poke holes all over cake (opposite end of a wooden spoon works great). Drizzle entire can of milk over top of cake.
Fill holes and pour all over.
Let milk soak in and do the same with caramel topping as with the milk.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top of cake with smashed up candy bars.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Heat corn syrup to boiling.
Combine egg whites, salt and vanilla in bowl.
Beat until egg whites are stiff.
Slowly pour in boiling syrup continuing to beat until frosting is fluffy and hangs in peaks.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove the chicken from the bone; chop in small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients with chicken and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix together pineapple, cherries and coconut.
Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Add pecans.
Top with margarine. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill 3 or 4 hours, until set.
Top with pie filling.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, cooking oil, salt and pepper. Pour over drained beans and toss well.
Refrigerate overnight. Drain before serving.
Serve on chopped lettuce in salad bowl.

title: corn chips(fritos)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In measuring cup or bowl, add boiling water to oil.
Stir together and pour onto dry mixture all at once.
Quickly gather into soft dough and divide in half.
Roll out on cookie sheet very thin.
Score and bake at 350° until light brown around edges.
Serves 16.

title: zucchini freezer jam
directions: Cook zucchini 6 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cook 6 minutes.
Pour into 1/2 pint jars or pints.
Seal and turn upside down.
Let stand 24 hours.
Freeze.

title: linguine with tomatoes and basil
directions: Combine tomatoes, Brie, basil, garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Set aside, covered, at room temperature for 2 to 4 hours.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat all until creamy.
Frost cooled cake.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Pour in 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Spread 1/2 cookie dough in 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased with butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over dough.
Spread remaining dough over filling.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat egg.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Sift flour and
baking powder together; add egg mixture, apples and nuts.
Put in greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, shortening and eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients and separate into 3 parts.
Roll each part in long rolls in wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: country-style cube steak
directions: Coat meat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper; brown in oil with onion and green pepper.
Stir in brown sugar, mustard, catsup, water, vinegar and Worcestershire.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serves 4.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add baking soda and salt.
Sift into measuring bowl.
Add butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar; cut with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Remove 1/2 cup and set aside.
Combine egg and buttermilk; add to dry ingredients and beat to blend.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan; combine chopped bars, nuts and reserved crumbs and sprinkle over the top of batter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: fried tomatoes in milk gravy
directions: Fry bacon and remove from frying pan.
Dredge sliced tomatoes in 1/2 cup flour, salt and pepper.
Fry.
Make milk gravy with last three ingredients.
Place fried tomatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish; add crumbled bacon and cover with milk gravy and serve.

title: chess cakes
directions: Melt on low heat the oleo and light brown sugar.
Remove from heat; put in mixing bowl and beat in, in this order: 1/2 cup sugar, 4 eggs (one at a time), flour mixture, vanilla and pecans. Cut into bars while warm and roll in powdered sugar.
Keeps well in airtight container.

title: sea island bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan on very low heat.
Remove.
Blend in sugar and stir in flour, then add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add nuts, coconut, chocolate and stir to combine.
Pour into pan and bake 30 minutes. Cool in pan and cut in squares.

title: banana crunch punch
directions: Heat sugar in water just until it dissolves.
Add remaining juices to mixture.
Mash bananas or put in blender.
Add to mixture.
Mixture can be frozen in plastic containers.
Thaw the frozen mixture until it is slushy, then add ginger ale.
Makes 60 servings.

title: eggnog
directions: Also you will need a rotary eggbeater.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift 3 times with next 4 ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add molasses; beat well.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Pour into 8-inch square pan or 7 x 11 1/2-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Excellent.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place small amount of chicken down center of tortillas.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons of salsa over chicken and roll up; place the seamed side down in baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over tortillas.
Cover with thinly sliced cheese; cook until it melts and bubbles.
Do not brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salt water until tender.
When cool, cut into small pieces.
Cook celery, onion and bell pepper in mushroom soup.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mix thoroughly the chicken pieces with all other ingredients, including spaghetti and mushroom soup.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into casserole; cover with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Add second layer of mixture; cover with remaining cheese.
Put into a 325° oven; bake until cheese is melted.
Serves 8 people.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Add extra egg, if dropped cookie is desired.
Add 2 tablespoons sour cream if a soft dropped cookie is desired.

title: artichoke and crab dip(microwave recipe)
directions: Mix chopped artichokes and crab with cheese and mayonnaise in a 2-quart glass dish.
Microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes, stirring once, until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: creamed clams over linguine
directions: Open cans of clams; reserve clams.
Mix clam juice with milk until it makes 2 cups.
Melt margarine in a skillet; add chopped onion and simmer until onion is soft.
Add flour and mix with onion.
Add the milk and clam juice mixture and cook until the sauce is thickened.
Add clams, mushrooms and Mrs. Dash seasoning to taste.
Add parsley before serving over linguine.
Also sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top before serving.

title: sweet and sour cucumbers
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 45 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Make one hour before serving or up to 2 days ahead.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and brown; drain well.
Line bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with crescent rolls (pinch perforations to seal).
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over sausage.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Blend pineapple and bananas until smooth.
Add water, sugar, lemonade and orange juice.
Freeze.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.
Then add cold ginger ale.

title: linguini with white clam sauce and broccoli
directions: Start cooking linguini according to package directions.
While linguini cooks, make sauce.
In a heavy 2-quart saucepan cook oil and garlic about one minute over moderate heat, until garlic just starts to turn golden.
Add clam liquid, parsley, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to moderately low and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low, stir in clams and heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile, when linguini is almost cooked, add broccoli to the pot and cook a few minutes, until tender but still firm.
Drain linguini and broccoli in a colander.
Put into a large warmed shallow bowl and pour clam sauce over pasta.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef; stir in onion, tomatoes, chilies and chili powder.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with 6 tortillas; spread meat mixture over tortillas and top with the remaining tortillas.
Sprinkle grated cheese over tortillas.
Heat soup with 1/4 cup of water to make pouring consistency.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and taco sauce.

title: mom's best cheese cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour and baking powder.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Go all the way up the sides and corners to the top.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese with milk and gradually add sugar.
Blend well and mix in vanilla.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain 2 cans yellow hominy.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup. Saute 1 medium onion in 1/2 stick oleo.
Add Cheez Whiz (for a milder taste, use 1/2 jar jalapeno and 1/2 jar plain Cheez Whiz). Mix all together.
Pour into casserole dish (2-quart).
Top with crushed corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: like stuff cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil lightly.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
(May like a little more sauce.)

title: angel food cake roll
directions: Mix angel food cake as directed.
Pour half cake mixture onto a jelly roll pan (or shallow cookie sheet) that has been greased and lined with wax paper, also greasing wax paper.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Sprinkle powdered sugar onto a cotton towel and invert cake onto this, carefully removing wax paper.
Roll cake up and allow to cool.

title: microwave cheese shrimp puffs
directions: Arrange crackers on napkin-lined plates.
In bowl, microwave butter for 10 seconds to soften.
Add cheese and blend.
Stir in egg yolk and shrimp.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar together, then gradually add sugar.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; mix well.
Form meat mixture into small balls.
Brown lightly in small amount of butter, then bake in oven at 350° until firm and brown.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan combine first 3 ingredients; gradually stir in milk.
Add butter, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; remove from heat. Stir in the next 3 ingredients.
Toss vegetables.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping and bake for 20 minutes.

title: company pickle chunks
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water.
Let stand until next morning.
Drain.
Repeat this procedure next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling and pour over cucumbers. Let stand two days. On the third day, bring to boiling the cucumbers and liquid.
Seal in hot jars.
(It is best to use a stone crock for soaking.)

title: cranberry jello salad(heritage recipe)
directions: Dissolve Jello in water. Liquify cranberry sauce and hot water in blender. Mix rest of ingredients together and let jell in oblong dish.

title: phillippine flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except steak.
Add steak and marinate 12 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Broil a few minutes on each side until medium or medium-rare.
Do not overcook.
Slice diagonally across the grain in very thin slices.
Serves 4.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg (beaten) and pecans together and press in bottom of buttered glass dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool in dish and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: confetti shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; lightly dust with flour.
Combine eggs, cream, salt and pepper; dip shrimp into mixture, then roll in coconut.
Deep fry in hot oil (375°) about 3 minutes.
Serve immediately with apricot or plum sauce.

title: old-fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup in large saucepan until soft ball stage (235° to 240°).
Add peanuts and butter.
Continue cooking until hard ball stage (300° to 310°).
Keep stirring.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and vanilla, stirring rapidly.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add broth from turkey or chicken until dressing is as thin as you like.
Will thicken when baked.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot spiced wine
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir to dissolve sugar or honey.
Heat to just below boiling point.
Mull for at least 15 minutes.
Strain, if desired.
Serve in large mugs.

title: tortoni squares
directions: Combine almonds, butter, crumbs and extract.
Remove 1/3 cup of this mixture and set aside.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to boil over low heat, stirring
occasionally.
Pour over vegetables, stirring gently to blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour on top of melted butter.
Mix 1 tablespoon flour with peaches and juice.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Place sugar in bowl.
Add cooking oil and eggs; beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture and blend in vanilla.
Add pecans and apples.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve warm and topped with ice cream or whipped cream.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Bake pie shell 5 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Spread chopped ham on bottom, then add chopped Swiss cheese over ham.
Combine light cream, salt and eggs.
Blend mixture until smooth.
Pour mixture over ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Add salt, baking powder, flour and water.
Stir until moistened.
Roll out.
Let dry and cut.
Now cook.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla together until fluffy. Add egg yolks.

title: spice cake
directions: Stir flour and sugar together.
Add spices and mix well.
Add eggs and oil.
Mix in baby food.
Pour in prepared tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sister's blueberry dessert
directions: Place blueberries on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer pineapple over berries.
Put sugar over top.
Sprinkle cake mix over.
Drizzle melted butter over.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: In top of a double boiler, saut onion and green pepper in butter (both chopped).
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese has melted.
Serve hot with crackers or party rye.

title: eddie's own hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and store.
Use as wish.
Mix 1/2 cup of mixture with 1/2 cup hot water.

title: sausage dipnederland, texas
directions: Brown sausage, then add beef and onion and brown both.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to boil while stirring; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add jar of marshmallow and 12 ounce jar of peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan and let cool.

title: ham rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook asparagus as directed on package; drain.
Wrap each ham slice around 2 to 3 asparagus spears. Place in an ungreased baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Mix soup and wine; pour over ham rolls.
Bake, uncovered, until bubbly for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls into medium-hot oil.
When bottom turns golden brown, turn and brown the other side.
Serves 8.

title: microwave sugar pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, mix well.
Then add the rest.
Cook approximately 9 to 12 minutes in the microwave.
Stir while cooking.
The mixture will bubble up and when it is thick like pudding, pour into a baked (9-inch) pie shell.
Time in the microwave may vary according to bowl size and microwaves.
Make only 1 pie at a time.

title: danish butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add and beat egg yolks.
Add flour.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Use cookie cutters and decorate as desired.
Cook at 375° until golden brown.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in zucchini.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chocolate chips and nuts.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Very moist.
Freezes well.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix crushed wafers, powdered sugar, and pecans.
Add butter and orange juice.
Mix well.
Roll out in small balls and then roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
(They freeze well.)

title: mamaw's pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, crushing herbs in hand.
Thin with a small amount of water to preference.
It is not necessary to heat this sauce before using to top the pizza.

title: lite cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix well for 2 minutes. Pour batter into a 9x13 greased & floured cake pan. Bake for 35-45 minutes at 350°. When cooled, frost with 1 can "low fat" fudge frosting.

title: purdue cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; dissolve soda in sour cream; add with all remaining ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey soup
directions: Boil chicken or turkey carcass 2 or 3 hours.
Remove bones and salvage as much meat as possible from the bones and add back to chicken or turkey stock.
Then add all the above ingredients and cook until well done.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Bring to a boil and cook until thick (about 5 minutes).
Let cool.

title: whole wheat health bread
directions: Mix flour, cracked wheat and oats.
Combine 3 cups flour mixture, wheat germ, sunflower seeds, yeast and salt.
Mix water (120°), cottage cheese, molasses, honey and oil.
Add to 3 cups of flour mixture.
Beat 3 minutes with electric mixer.
Stir in rest of flour.
Rest 10 minutes.
Knead 10 minutes.
Place in oiled bowl, covered.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Shape into 3 or 4 loaves. Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Pour over other ingredients after combining them.

title: raisin bars
directions: Combine and boil for 3 minutes, raisins, shortening, salt, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cool.
Add flour, soda, nuts and vanilla.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Can be plain or frosted.

title: banana split salad
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and Cool Whip.
Fold in pie filling, bananas, pineapple and nuts.

title: chicken apple saute
directions: Dip apple slices in mix of 1/2 water and lemon or lime juice. Heat oil in nonstick skillet.
Saute chicken until no longer pink and remove from pan.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery until tender-crisp.
Return chicken to pan; cook for 1 minute.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to mixture.
Cook until sauce thickens. Makes 3 servings.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Mix warm potatoes with sugar, salt and shortening.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Roll on bread board to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter and place on floured baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: pat's chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and flour in medium saucepan.
Set aside. Beat yolks.
Gradually stir yolks and milk into mix. Add butter. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly. Remove and add vanilla.
Put into shell.
Beat egg whites.
Wait 6 minutes. Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Split shrimp and season with salt, black pepper and cayenne. Set aside.
Melt oleo or oil and add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook slowly in uncovered heavy pot until onions are wilted.
Add seasoned shrimp; let simmer, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to mixture. Cook 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: deviled clams
directions: Scrub the clams and open with a shucking knife, or place in a baking pan.
Bake in 300° oven until shells open enough to remove clam, reserving the broth.
Do not bake the clams!
Remove the clams from shells and chop up or use the frozen or canned ones. Oil the inside of the scrubbed clam shells.
Mix the remaining ingredients together until well blended, then divide among the shells.
Place them in a shallow baking pan and bake in preheated 375° oven until golden brown, approximately 25 minutes.
If pan-frying, place the filled clam shells upside down in a large heated and buttered saucepan and fry, covered, over medium heat until golden brown, approximately 8 minutes.
Yields 12 deviled clams (I usually serve 2 per person).
These are delicious either baked or pan-fried.

title: southwestern gourmet salad
directions: Heat chili powder in olive oil for 2 minutes; remove from heat and add Tabasco, Worcestershire, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Stir into beans and let stand for 30 minutes to several hours.
Mix other ingredients into beans when cold and chill until ready to serve.
Before serving, line bowl with broken lettuce and place bean mixture in center.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Place melted butter in a shallow dish or pie pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except chicken, in another shallow dish. Roll chicken pieces in melted butter, coating each evenly, then roll in crumb mixture, coating each completely.
Place chicken pieces about 1 inch apart on rack of broiler pan.
Broil in preheated broiler, turning once halfway through cooking time, until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork, 25 to 40 minutes.

title: mama's noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles until tender; drain and rinse noodles with hot water (tap water).
Add 2 sticks of margarine to noodles and sugar.
Beat eggs; add noodles, sour cream and cottage cheese. Mix well.
Grease Pyrex baking dish with margarine.
Pour mixture in dish.
Take corn flakes crumbled, add 1/2 stick margarine and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle over top of pudding.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes after pudding starts to cook.

title: lasagne by ellen
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and garlic salt.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Dip chicken into butter and roll in crumb mixture.
Bake uncovered fat 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter and add flour, stirring until smooth. Add onion and cook until soft.
Add liquid and stir to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and until melted.
Combine with spinach. Place in casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
This freezes well.
Serves 6.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients. Roll level tbsp into balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork. bake at 350° for 10-12 min. makes about 2 dozen.

title: overnight coffeecake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter with sugars until smooth.
Add eggs and buttermilk; beat until slightly fluffy.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; mix well.

title: fruit pie
directions: Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 1 pie.

title: soft banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Add egg, mashed bananas, nuts, rolled oats and raisins.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
If you like a frosted cookie, frost while the cookies are warm with an icing of confectioners sugar, shortening, milk and vanilla.
These cookies freeze well.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beat well with electric mixer.
Add cream cheese, beat until light and fluffy.
Alternate adding flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar until sticky.
Pour over remaining ingredients; stir good.
Chill.

title: pecan pie 2
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, syrup, and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: white cake
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add remaining ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes on low and 1 1/2 minutes on high.
Add unbeaten egg whites.
Beat another 1/2 minute.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Cook
and stir sugar and syrup until mixture comes to a full rolling
boil.
Remove
from heat and cool; then stir in Carnation milk.
Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: iowa ham balls
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine ham, beef, eggs, milk and graham cracker crumbs.
Using a 1/3 cup measure, shape mixture into 2-inch balls.
Place in two large shallow roasting pans. Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, basting frequently with sauce.
Yield:
about 15 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt sugar and syrup together.
Bring to boiling point, then turn off heat.
Add peanut butter and let melt.
Add corn flakes. Drop on wax paper and shape into balls.

title: death by chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Chop 1 (8 oz.) package of chocolate and set aside.
Microwave the remaining squares until melted (at 30 second intervals, mixing after each to prevent burning) and mix until smooth.
Stir in sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder and stir until well blended.
Stir in chopped chocolate and nuts.
Drop by 1/4 cup-fuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12-13 minutes or until cookies are puffed and feel set to the touch.
Cool on cookie sheet for one minute, then transfer to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread the pineapple into a greased 10 x 12-inch pan.
Spread the cake mix over the pineapple; scatter the pecans over the cake mix and top with butter pieces.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and cinnamon over low heat until it forms small bubbles.
Remove from heat and stir in crumbs.
Press in 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in milk, 1/3 cup lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Line crust with 3 sliced bananas.
Turn filling into crust and chill until firm.
Dip 2 sliced bananas in 2 tablespoons lemon juice and place on top of pie.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes.
Stir.
Serve over fruit, gingerbread or ice cream.

title: festive rice
directions: In a medium nonstick saucepan, bring broth to boil.
Add rice. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in 4 tablespoons Molly McButter and all vegetables.
Cover, continue cooking 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Sprinkle with remaining Molly McButter and pepper to taste.
Fluff with fork and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese spinach puffs
directions: Combine first two ingredients.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain all liquid.
Combine next six ingredients.
Add spinach and muffin mix and stir well.
Cover and chill for one hour.
Form batter into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve warm.

title: low cholesterol apple and oat bran muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour, oat bran, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Set aside. In a small bowl, combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moist.
Stir in apple.
Store batter tightly covered in refrigerator for 5 days.
To bake, spray muffin cups with nonstick spray coating.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup.
Bake 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Make 12 muffins. 124 calories per muffin.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: In medium saucepan bring carrots, honey and 1 cup water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover with lid slightly ajar and simmer until water is evaporated and carrots are tender, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortoni
directions: Combine almonds, butter, vanilla wafer crumbs and almond extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Line an 8-inch square or round pan with aluminum foil.
Sprinkle 1/2 crumbs on bottom.
Spread 1/2 of ice cream over crumb layer. Spread 1/2 of apricot preserves over ice cream mixture.
Repeat; sprinkle top with reserved crumbs.
Cover with foil.
Place in freezer.
Makes 9 generous servings.

title: delicious brat casserole
directions: Saute celery until partially done.
In well buttered 2-quart casserole dish, place potatoes, thinly sliced.
Cut brats into 1-inch pieces and cook thoroughly.
Drain grease off and place on top of sliced potatoes.
Place celery and green beans over brats. Mix milk with soup.
Stir well and pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour covered and 30 more minutes uncovered.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Melt margarine over potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Place in oven; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or at 400° for 1 hour.
When potatoes are tender, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and stir. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Will serve 4 hearty eaters.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix
Kool-Aid
and sugar well.	Dissolve mixture in hot water. Add cold water and orange juice.
Chill until ready to serve. Add
Seven-Up
and	strawberries
just before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: citrus-beer punch
directions: Remove peel from the 6 lemons and set aside.
Juice lemons. You should have about 2 cups juice.
In a large saucepan, stir together sugar and water.
Bring to boiling.
Add reserved lemon peel.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove and discard peel.
Add lemon juice and grapefruit juice to sugar mixture.
Transfer to a 2 1/2 to 3-quart pitcher; cover and chill completely.

title: international aid stew
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 300° to 350° for 4 hours.
Keep covered for entire baking time.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar with butter and graham crackers.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour over crackers and bake for 25 minutes.
Let cool. Spread pie mix on top of mix and top with Cool Whip.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice
carrots	and cook until tender.	Drain and cool. Alternate layers of carrots, pepper and onions.
Blend remaining ingredients
and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil in bowl.
Add dry zucchini; stir and add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Makes two loaves.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Mix well and pour into baking dish.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy blueberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add blueberries and gently mix.
Place in one of the pie crusts.
Top with other pie crust. Let crust set at room temperature so it is easy to handle.
Pinch edges together with fingers or fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: chewy shortbread bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Combine flour and sugar.
Using pastry blender, cut in oleo until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into a greased pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Meanwhile, combine eggs, brown sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in soda, walnuts, raisins and coconut.
Spoon over hot crust.
Spread to cover evenly.
Return to oven; bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until top is set.
Cool completely and cut into 20 bars.

title: bagogi
directions: Slice roast thin and marinate overnight.
Grill meat and reserve the marinade for dipping meat in or to pour over steamed rice.

title: michelle's thumbprint cookies
directions: Add the first 4 ingredients and mix them thoroughly.
Sift together and stir in flour and salt.
Make into balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in nuts, if desired.
Bake 5 minutes in 375° oven.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Cut celery 3 to 4-inches long.
Mix all the preceding.
Use decorating tube to fill.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano.
Then add tomato sauce and simmer.
Cook lasagna noodles and blanch in cold water.
Grease baking dish.
Beat eggs; add cottage cheese.
Line baking dish with noodles; cover with meat sauce, then cottage cheese, then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: italian vegetable cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Use 2 quart baking dish.
Combine eggplant, tomatoes. zucchini, artichoke hearts and cheese.
In small non-stick skillet, heat oil and add garlic.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Mix in pasta sauce.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Cover and bake 45 minutes. Cool slightly. Serve.

title: maui onions baked with chicken and broccoli(this is an original recipe)
directions: Place half the broccoli in a greased baking dish and season with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Preheat skillet on medium heat; add butter and onions.
Saute until onions are translucent.
Add onions to sour cream and place 1/2 of the mixture on prepared broccoli.
Then top with half the chicken and half the cheese.
Repeat for second layer, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: hot sausage cheese puffs
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet, breaking up the meat. Cook until no longer pink; drain and let cool. Add sausage to large mixing bowl and add cheese, Bisquick mix and water. Mix well until blended. Roll into 1-inch balls and place 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 400° oven for approximately 10 minutes or until puffed and slightly browned. Cool completely. Best when dipped in pizza sauce.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, butter, oil, egg and vanilla in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well until blended. Stir in cereal, oatmeal and pecans.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on greased cookie sheet 1-inch apart; flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Pour nuts and chips in unbaked pie shell.
Beat eggs, sugar, syrup and butter together.
Pour over nuts and chips and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread evenly on bottom half of buns.
Broil until meat is cooked and edges of buns are toasting. Watch very closely.
During last 2 minutes put 2 strips of cheese crisscrossed on top of each bun.
Brown tops of buns.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Toss with 2 tablespoons flour. Sift together remaining flour, baking soda, powder and salt. Cream butter and gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and bananas, alternating in 3 parts.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done. Makes one loaf.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press together the crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan (17 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch).
If there is extra dough, you can make a square and put it in a pie pan or whatever you might have. Bake according to directions until golden brown; cool.
Beat the cream cheese, dry dressing and mayonnaise with mixer.
Mix and spread onto cooled crust.
Add chopped raw vegetables, cut fine, to cover.
You may use any variation of the following:
carrots, cauliflower, green and red peppers, onions, broccoli, fresh mushrooms, red and white radishes, celery, green and black olives and cucumbers.
Grated sharp cheese and eggs may also be used, if desired.
Sprinkle celery seed over all.
Slightly press all vegetables into the mixture with a spatula when finished.
Make the day before; cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, cheese and milk until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder; spoon over biscuits.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add soup, enchilada sauce and milk.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
In a lasagna dish layer sauce and tortilla shells with the first layer being sauce.
Place cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish servings with lettuce, tomato, etc.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening. Add milk last.
Press in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef over medium-high heat.
Drain fat.
Add onions and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into a large kettle or roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: low-fat lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar and lemon juice. Beat well.
Pour in Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Cook according to directions on cake box.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Mix powdered sugar and enough lemon juice to make thick paste.
Pour on warm cake.

title: baked chili rellenos
directions: Slip a strip of cheese in each chili pepper.
Arrange 1/2 of chilies in baking dish; sprinkle with half of grated cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Carefully pour egg, milk and flour mixture over all.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: buffet cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Thaw potatoes.
Combine in a large bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan casserole and top with cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mad hatter meatballs
directions: Saute the green pepper and onion in the butter until tender. Stir in the soups and water.
Heat to boiling, then simmer. Combine the remaining ingredients and shape into balls.
Drop meatballs into sauce and cook, slowly, for 1 hour.
Good served with rice.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar gradually; beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pecans; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and waxed paper-lined 8-inch cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes; cool.

title: spicy bean salad
directions: Cook fresh beans in boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from boiling water and plunge into ice water until cold.
Drain.
In large bowl, combine green beans, pinto beans, butter beans and red onion rings.
In jar with tight fitting lid, combine vinegar, oil, garlic, sugar and red chili pepper flakes.
Shake well.
Pour dressing over salad.
Stir and cover.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until chilled.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates, if desired.

title: kraft cheese
directions: Work soda in
the
dry
cheese
curds.
Melt butter in pan. Add cheese curds;
stir
constantly until cheese is melted and smooth.
Add the hot cream, a
little at a time.
Add salt last. Pour in box or pan suitable for
slicing.
Cheese
making
is delicate and does not always turn out.
We
found
this
recipe good
as a spreading cheese when it didn't get slicing consistency.

title: melvin's cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomatoes and let set overnight. Add tomatoes right before serving.

title: chicken or turkey turnovers
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in small saucepan of salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
In a bowl, stir together cream cheese, milk and pepper until smooth.
Fold in meat and cooked vegetables.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Seal perforations to form 4 rectangles.
Put filling mixture in center of rectangle.
Pull corners to point over center and pinch to seal around mixture.
Place turnovers on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Mix soups, sour cream and onion in large bowl.
Add frozen hash browns and toss to coat evenly.
Place mixture in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
If desired, mix cornflakes and melted butter. Sprinkle over the mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 30 minutes or until done.

title: angel sweetie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat; blend in egg.
Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows.
Blend well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill.
Recipe makes about 48.

title: mom's shepherd's pie
directions: Layer in casserole dish.
Break up hamburg and cook until brown; drain off fat.
(Season with garlic and onion powders.) Put drained hamburg on bottom of casserole dish.
Put drained corn on top of hamburg.
Put tomato soup on top of corn.
Put mashed potatoes (make instant according to box) on top of tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Pour jello in water and stir.
Add lemon juice and gelatin. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
When set, cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Wash zucchini.
Blend together sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
(Save some flour to toss pecans.)
Beat and mix well.
Add floured pecans.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except pie mix.
Spread half in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pie mix on top and spread with rest of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drizzle powdered sugar frosting on top.

title: pickled fish(very good)
directions: Soak cut-up fish in salt brine (use 1/2 cup salt to 2 gallons water) for 24 to 48 hours.
Turn several times a day.
Drain fish and soak in white vinegar until fish turns white, 24 to 48 hours. If fish is fat, soak longer.

title: 7 day sweet pickle
directions: Clean cucumbers (leave whole).
Drop into hot water.
Repeat the following 3 days (total 4 days).
On the fifth day, slice crosswise 1/4-inch thick; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Drop cucumber slices in hot syrup.
Let set 2 days, turning to get all slices in syrup.
Heat and fill clean, hot jars.
Seal.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except biscuits.
Cook 6 to 7 biscuits according to directions.
Pour mixture over crumbled biscuits. Bake at 350° until a little brown.
Do not overcook.

title: chicken and pork adobo
directions: Place cut pork and chicken in a large saucepan.
Add vinegar, garlic, pepper, soy sauce, onion, bay leaves and water.
Cover and cook slowly until most of the sauce is evaporated.
Drain; save.
Separate the pieces of onion from the pork and chicken and saute in the lard until brown.
Add the pork and chicken and fry until brown.
Add the sauce and simmer for 5 minutes; serve hot. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cajun corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo.
When done, mix with corn and add seasoning.
Cover and heat in microwave for 10 minutes.
When 1/2 done, stir thoroughly and continue cooking until done.

title: flowerpot cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch flowerpot, hand shovel and silk flowers.

title: vinegar candy
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil mixture until brittle stage.
Pull and cut into small pieces.
Butter plate and wrap later.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain well.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese. Put in casserole dish in layers.
First, put half of broccoli in casserole dish.
Next, put 1/2 of soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese mix.
Repeat broccoli then cheese mix.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers; pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour (or less) at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: ma-ma's glorious potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour into pan.
Put crushed barbecue potato chips on top and bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: rice, sour cream, mushroom pilaf
directions: Saute mushrooms and peppers in pot until tender, not brown. Add water. Stir in seasoning packet. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice and sour cream.
Bring to a boil. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir before serving.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Saute butter, cabbage and onions until they are soft.
Cook noodles.
Add noodles to the mixture.
Toss them together and serve.

title: spicy apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend well, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tests done and cake begins to pull away from sides of pan. Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add vinegar, egg yolks and lemon, then hot water.
Cook and stir until it boils.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices of lemon; set aside.
Squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon; set aside.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim pork chops well and cut a deep slash in the meaty side of each chop.
Chop apples with peel, onion and celery rather fine.
Mix with parsley, salt, pepper, sage and thyme.
Spoon as much stuffing as possible into each pocket; do not tie or skewer.
Place in buttered baking dish with cover or use foil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sage.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours.
Remove cover and bake another 20 minutes or until chops are brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients and microwave 2 minutes on High.
Stir into oil mixture and mix well the Hidden Valley Ranch powder.
Pour over pretzels evenly and stir occasionally for 1 hour so pretzels will be seasoned.
Put into container and cover.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add chopped onion.
Let onion brown, then add meat, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until meat turns brown.
Pour rice into casserole dish, then beef consomme, salt and pepper to taste.
Then add browned meat (dip out of margarine).
Cover and cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: gooey caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar and Karo until sugar is dissolved; stir occasionally.
Add margarine and milk.
Cook (stir occasionally) until firm ball stage.
Add the soda; this will foam up.
Stir and pour over the air popped corn.

title: country apple meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup. Shape into loaf.
Cover with catsup. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chess pie no. 2
directions: Cream butter with spoon.
Add sugar and mix well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in egg yolks and then the milk gradually.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes.

title: coffee cake(made easy)
directions: Pull off pieces of dough; roll in melted butter, sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Put in round cake pan or bread pan.
Let raise 45 minutes, approximately.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Let stand, uncovered, at room temperature for 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in large kettle; bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables; heat thoroughly, but don't boil.
Pack at once into hot sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Add 2 cups sugar to apples.
Mix sugar, butter and eggs together.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to the apple mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pans and bake in a 300 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese lime pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese at medium speed until smooth. Beat in 1/2 cup of milk.
Reduce mixing speed to low and add pudding mix (undiluted), limeade concentrate and the remaining milk.
Beat until blended.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Spoon mixture into the prepared graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate pie until firm enough to slice, at least 4 hours.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour water over shortening.
Add molasses, sugar and egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch square pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan. Cut into squares and serve with Cool Whip.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies. Mix jello in boiling water according to directions. Pour jello over Twinkies.

title: cereal christmas trees(from betty crocker cookbook)
directions: In large saucepan, heat butter and marshmallows over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and food color.
Fold in cereal until evenly coated.

title: elephant tracks
directions: Combine scalded milk, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in egg.
Add flour; work until smooth.
Put dough on floured board; let rest 10 minutes.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough out into rectangular shape; brush with butter.
Sprinkle with some of the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Roll and cut slices 1-inch thick.
Put a generous amount of sugar on board.
Roll each slice until flat, 5 to 6-inch circle.
Put on greased baking sheet and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Blend tomatoes at a low speed until smooth, one can at a time. Return to cans.
Heat the olive oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and parsley.
Saute until you can smell garlic.
Add tomatoes slowly.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, stir in salt and pepper and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 35 to 40 minutes or until thick.

title: finksa kakor(finnish cakes)
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and almond flavor.
Stir in flour.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Chill dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips 2 1/2 inches long and 3/4 inches wide.
Brush tops with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar and almonds mixture.
Carefully transfer several strips at a time to ungreased baking sheet.
Bake just until delicately golden brown at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with bread, buttered side up.
Spread sausage evenly over bread.

title: can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Stir together the 3 ingredients until mixed.
Drop by spoonful into greased cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Wait 5 minutes before you remove from sheet.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Wrap chicken with cheese.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish (glass).
Pour soup over top.
Melt butter.
Pour 1/2 butter over soup, then dressing over top (dry).
Then drizzle remaining butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick taco pie
directions: In large pan, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, water and olives; simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 9-inch pie pan, pressing to form a crust.
Sprinkle 1/2 of corn chips over bottom of crust. Spoon meat mixture over crust and corn chips.
Spread sour cream over mixture and cover with cheese and then remaining corn chips. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: carb free potato salad
directions: Break cauliflower up and steam in single layers for 5 minutes in microwave, stopping half way to stir.
Cool completely, then cut in bite size pieces.
Peel and chop hard boiled eggs; add celery and onion and an other vegetables you would ordinarily put in your potato salad.
Mix mayonnaise or miracle whip and mustard (if preferred) to desired consistency adding salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with paprika and enjoy with no carb guilt!
Close your eyes, you will never know the difference.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli part way.
Arrange in greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
In separate bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over this, then top with bread crumbs and butter mixture and sprinkle parsley over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in either 2 layers, oblong 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix all ingredients and cook on crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: no-fat low-salt soup
directions: In a large pot, mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover 5 minutes.
Simmer for one hour, checking water level occasionally.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients together except rice.
Bring mixture to boil; add rice.
Turn off heat and cover until rice is done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs sprinkled with butter.
Return to oven for a few more minutes.

title: cranberry whip
directions: Mix all together.
Add Dream Whip last.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large black skillet, melt butter in oven until completely melted.
Remove skillet and swirl around butter so that bottom and sides are covered.
In separate mixing bowl, put all remaining ingredients and mix gently.
Pour mixture into skillet with butter.
Do not stir!
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until crust is golden.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream. Transfer leftovers to airtight container.
Reheat in microwave. Better the next day!

title: butterscotch pecan rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, 1 tablespoon sugar, salt and shortening; cool.
In medium bowl, combine warm water, remaining 1 tablespoon sugar and yeast.
Add cooled milk mixture, egg, lemon rind and about 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Knead in remaining flour until dough springs back when indented, not very long.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Roll out; spread with 1 1/2 tablespoons melted margarine.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and milk well.
Add cream cheese. Blend well. Add powdered sugar. Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Fill pie crust. Freeze and serve frozen. You can drizzle chocolate syrup over top.

title: cheese & rice casserole
directions: Get some pork- or veal- Schnitzel.
Wash the meat; dry with a paper towel and rub with pepper, salt and just a little brown sugar.
Cook in (real) butter in an open pan on both sides until the meat is done and takes on a nice brown.
Set aside and keep hot.

In the meat juice left in the pan, cook fresh mushrooms (about a pound for 2 Schnitzel; any kind of mushrooms will work, but the white mushrooms you get in any supermarket or, if you collect your own, a mix of wild forest mushrooms, seem to be best) until the liquid is mostly gone, adding pepper, salt and small amount of sugar if desired (too much will spoil the mushrooms) to taste.
Stir in fresh cream (unwhipped) until you get a thick sauce.
Pour on top of the Schnitzel.
Serve with french fries or croquettes.

title: senator russell's pumpkin
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into oblong Pyrex dish and cover with topping.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: Slice cookie dough into 3/4-inch slices. Cut each slice into quarters. Place each quarter into ungreased 1 1/4-inch muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. (Dough will rise during baking.) Remove from the oven and immediately press a Reese's cup into each cookie. Cool before removing from pan. Refrigerate until firm. Yields 4 dozen.

title: sunday spice cake
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, flour, cloves, allspice, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, molasses,
Crisco and milk (2/3 cup).
Beat 2 minutes.
Then add baking powder, soda, eggs and 1/2 cup milk. Mix for 2 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Add the oil, pineapple, vanilla, eggs and bananas.
The mixture is stirred to blend, not beaten.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Cool completely in pan before removing.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Use as a substitute for eggs.
Yield:
1 serving equivalent to 2 eggs.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook margarine according to directions.
Drain.
Beat eggs in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Mix in cooked macaroni and the cheese; stir well.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 8 to 10 .

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a mixer bowl and mix slowly for 1 minute.
Turn mixer to medium speed and beat for 10 full minutes. Put into a well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: checca with shrimp
directions: Cook pasta and set aside.
Heat oil and garlic in skillet until garlic is golden brown.
Add stewed tomatoes and simmer for 1 minute.
Add basil and season with salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and cook for 2 more minutes.
Toss over pasta.
Serves 4 to 6. This can be made with or without shrimp, or with sliced chicken breast.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 3/4-inch slices.
Dip into egg, then into bread crumbs or flour to coat, then carefully into egg mixture and into bread crumbs again.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add tomato slices and cook slowly, until brown on both sides and until tomato is tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: strawberry refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Mix cake per box instructions and bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cold water.
While cake is still warm, poke deep holes through top of cake with meat fork, toothpick or skewer about 1 inch apart.
Slowly drizzle jello over cake.
Cool in refrigerator.
To serve, top with whipped cream. Add fresh berries and nuts, if desired.

title: hearty cabbage soup
directions: In a flameproof casserole with a tight fitting lid, layer bread, cabbage, onions and garlic.
Spoon in tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Carefully pour stock into casserole so as not to disturb layers.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 30 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 4 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In medium skillet, brown sausage; remove and drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat; cook and stir onion and green pepper in reserved fat until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in drained sausage.
Spoon into partially baked shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In medium bowl, beat eggs until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes; cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine the corn flakes and melted oleo.
Put half in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add the cabbage.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the cabbage.
Sprinkle remaining corn flakes over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Beat together the peanut butter and margarine.
