Add sugar, stirring until well combined. Gently stir in Holiday Rice Krispies cereal.
Press dough evenly into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Chill in refrigerator about 30 minutes.

title: butterflied lamb in mustard sauce
directions: Split 1 hogie roll.
Remove about 2 tablespoons of bread crumbs from middle of roll.
Cook 2 slices bacon crisp.
Paint inside of roll with mayonnaise.
Place bacon on roll, then 4 oysters (raw) on top of bacon.
Roll and seal in aluminum foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Slice in thirds and serve.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Fill large pot one-half full of water with 3 bags of shrimp/crab boil, 2 beers, squeeze lemon and lime in and throw in rinds.
Bring to hard boil and let boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sausage and cook 12 minutes.
Then add corn to sausage and cook another 8 minutes.	Then add shrimp to corn and sausage and cook 6 minutes.
DO NOT OVERCOOK THE SHRIMP.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl first 6 ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Form balls and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken mushroom
directions: Place
chicken	thighs	(skin
removed)
in baking pan. Bake at	350°
for 1 hour.
Mix can of cream of mushroom soup with
3 tablespoons
shoyu.
Pour mixture over chicken thighs after 1 hour, then cook 15 minutes more.

title: ice cream
directions: In large bowl, stir together milk and syrup.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into an aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Cover; freeze 6 hours or until firm.

title: caramel filled chocolate cookies
directions: In small bowl, mix flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Blend well. In a large bowl, beat 1 cup of sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape about 1 tablespoonful of dough around 1 Rolo candy covering completely. Roll balls in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 375° or until set and slightly cracked.
Cool.

title: layered taco appetizer
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning mix.
Mix sour cream with avocado, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.
Grate cheese and shred lettuce and dice tomatoes.
Layer all ingredients on platter in order listed.
Serve with chips.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add onion soup.
Mix in tomato sauce and water. Cook 1/2 hour or longer.
Cook noodles until tender; drain and let sit in cold water until used.
Spread meat sauce in bottom of pan. Alternate noodles, sauce and cheese until all used.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Transfer meat to plate.
In same skillet, add remaining margarine and cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
Return meat to skillet; add water and steak sauce.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 50 to 60 minutes, until meat is tender.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: garden pie or quiche
directions: Steam the first 3 ingredients until tender.
Beat together milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt, pepper and thyme.
Grease a 9-inch pie tin, put vegetables in pie tin.
Spread shredded cheese over this. Pour Bisquick mixture over this.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes (ovens vary, so play it by ear).
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
If using cauliflower instead of broccoli, use 1/2 teaspoon curry powder instead of thyme.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Combine chopped apples and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Sift dry ingredients.
Blend oil, sugar and egg.
Blend the two mixtures; add chopped apple mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or topping.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Press out 1 roll of cookie mixture into brownie pan to cover bottom of pan evenly.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cookie layer.
Take other cookie roll and break off clumps of cookie dough.
Drop on top of mixture, scattering clumps all around. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Squares are done when cookie dough looks cooked and before cream cheese turns brown.
Cream cheese should look light beige.
Better to undercook.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip and Dream Whip thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crusts or chocolate crumb crusts.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first 6 ingredients together until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake until light brown.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and shortening in one cup of better than lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Mix flour and buttermilk.

title: home baked cheesy chicken and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven o 350 degrees.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Fold cheese into hot rice and stir to melt cheese.
Add milk and blend well.
Fold in chicken and broccoli. Pour into 1 2 qt. ovenproof casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes and serve.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Soften cheese over hot water.
Add gelatin and mix thoroughly. Heat ginger ale to boiling and slowly pour over cheese-gelatin mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Chill until syrupy.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Turn into 2-quart mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Makes 8 servings.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place the egg whites in top of double boiler.
Add all ingredients except vanilla.
Place over boiling water.
Have mixer in hand and start beating as soon as you place egg whites and other ingredients over boiling water.
Beat until thick and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Spread over 3 cake layers.

title: mrs. bailey's chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening. Add the remaining ingredients.
When cake is completely mixed, add 1 cup boiling water. Bake at 360° for 35 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Use either a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch pans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add oil and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes in 9 x 1`3 x 2-inch pan.

title: creamy vanilla frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat on low speed until well blended. Beat on high speed for 2 minutes, 1 or 2 drops of food coloring may be add.
This frosting works well in a decorator tube.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: plain boiled rice
directions: Wash rice 2 or 3 times, rubbing gently between the hands and drain very well.
Put rice and water into a saucepan of at least 2-quart capacity.
Cover and bring to a boil over a medium-high heat.
As soon as it is boiling, turn heat to medium-low and stir the rice with wooden spoon from the bottom up and around the edge. Scrape down the grains on the edge of pan.
Cover and let boil slowly until water is absorbed.
Stir gently once again and simmer over very low heat for 20 or 30 minutes.
Makes 4 cups cooked rice; 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese balls(appetizer)
directions: Melt butter.
Add slowly to flour.
Cheese block needs to be hand shredded.
Do not buy already shredded cheese.
It will not work with this recipe.

title: inspiration cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add egg whites and beat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Grease and lightly flour 2 (9-inch) spring-form pans.
Sprinkle bottom of pans with chopped walnuts; spoon 1/4 of batter into pans on top of nuts.
Sprinkle grated chocolate reserve over batter.
Pour remaining batter and spread evenly over chocolate layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: goof balls
directions: Put the condensed milk, confectioners sugar, coconut and nuts into a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill 3 hours. Roll into balls (about 1 teaspoon mixture).
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Melt chocolate and shortening in a double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Drop balls into chocolate mixture one at a time. Refrigerate until hard.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplants.
Soak in cold, salted water.
Drain and cook down in 3 tablespoons bacon grease until tender, about 2 hours.
In another pot, cook remaining ingredients.
Mix cooked eggplants and meat mixture together.
Add bread crumbs or rice to absorb liquid.
Bake at 350° until well heated.
Can be frozen.

title: toffee
directions: In saucepan, melt butter. Add sugar and nuts. Bring to 300° to 310°.
Pour into large cookie sheet with edges.
Spread evenly. Place Hershey bars on toffee and spread when melted.
Let cool.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Coat bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan with mayonnaise. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add remaining ingredients. Mix together well and pour into pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls; then roll balls in additional granulated sugar.
Place balls on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 - 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
While cooking, mix oatmeal and cocoa.
Add oatmeal and cocoa to ingredients.
Add vanilla before adding oatmeal and cocoa.
Drop out on wax paper.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Grease cake pan.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in Karo, water, salt and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boils and sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking (not stirring) until temperature reaches 260° or until a hard but plastic ball is formed.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flavoring (and coloring desired).

title: apple burritos
directions: Put apple pie mix in flour tortillas and roll up.
Place in pan.

title: easy-do potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and slice into logs.
Spray baking dish with Pam. Place potatoes in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: cherry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all together in microwave. Pour into pie shell (raw) and bake at 400° for 40 minutes until slightly brown.

title: easy pumpkin pie without a crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and pour into pie plate that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt 5 tablespoons margarine. Stir in brown sugar, water and pecans. Add maple flavoring and stir.

Separate each can crescent dough into 4 rectangles; seal perforations. Spread with the 8 tablespoons softened margarine. Combine cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over dough. Starting at shorter side, roll up each rectangle.	Cut each roll into 4 slices, forming 32 pieces. Place in prepared pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Invert immediately to remove from pan. Serve warm.
Makes 32 small rolls.

title: bread dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Old English cheese.
Add garlic salt.
Add enough beer to make thin consistency.
Hollow out bread.
Pour mix into bread.
Dip bread cubes in mix.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with crackers or bite sized fresh vegetables.
May be prepared 24 hours ahead to allow flavors to blend; store in refrigerator.
Reheat, covered with foil, for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix and spread in pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat concentrate in large mixer bowl on low speed for 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in ice cream; beat until blended. Gently stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat all ingredients and pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make 4 layers in a flowerpot ending with cookies.
Put a silk flower in the pot and add some gummy worms.

title: creamy bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in enough water to cover.
Cream butter and sugar well. Add yolks of eggs (if you want a meringue on top) or all of eggs (if you want a whiskey hard sauce).
Add milks, vanilla and salt.
Squeeze out bread well and put into mixture. Add raisins or fruit, if desired. Bake in a slow oven (about 200°) for 1 1/2 hours or until the pudding rises and is brown on top.
Make meringue and put on top
of pudding, running it into the oven for about 10 minutes.
Or make a whiskey sauce by mixing confectioners sugar with butter and whiskey to taste.

title: kielbasa, sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Cut kielbasa or sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Fry until well done.
Mix salt, flour and sugar together and blend with cold water.
Arrange layers of sliced potato, sliced apple and kielbasa or sausage in baking dish, pouring flour and sugar mixture over each layer.
Top with apples and kielbasa or sausage.
Add drippings.
Cover and bake at 375° until apples and potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 stew
directions: Place meat in a covered casserole.
Mix two soups together and add to meat.
No water, please!
Cover.
Place in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Serve over rice with French bread and a salad for a superb supper.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Sprinkle beef with meat tenderizer according to label directions; place in Dutch oven.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover pan tightly.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours or until beef is tender.
Make gravy from pan drippings if desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins, then add to butter and sugar mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until edges brown.
This recipe doubles or triples easily for big batches.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening and brown sugar well. Add molasses and egg. Mix well. Gradually blend in dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Fill press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown meat in 1 teaspoon hot oil.
Add all other ingredients, except potatoes, and simmer for 3 hours. If you are using potatoes, finely dice them and add after stew has cooked for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Reserve 2 cups of cake batter.
In remaining batter add 1 stick of melted margarine and 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk. Pour mixture into a large oblong cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Put caramels and the other stick of margarine and the rest of the Eagle Brand milk in double boiler and melt.
Add nuts and pour over cake that has been cooked.
Then pour remaining 2 cups of batter over caramel mixture and return to oven to finish baking.

title: koch kasse-german(cooked cheese)
directions: Put all ingredients into a saucepan and boil until all the cheese is melted.
Good as cheese spread.

title: pear crisp - kids in the kitchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place pears or apples in greased, shallow 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Pour water over your sliced pears or apples.

title: garlic oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers in large bowl.
Stir in dressing mix, dill weed, garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Pour oil over all; stir.
Let stand 1 hour.
Stir frequently until all oil is absorbed.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Mix eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Cook sausage; drain. Press rolls into circle in pizza pan.
Add sausage, potatoes, eggs, cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mile-high strawberry pie
directions: Crush berries.
Add sugar and let sit for 30 minutes.
Put berries, lemon juice and egg whites in large bowl and beat with electric mixer on medium speed until stiff peaks form.
(This may take 15 minutes.)
Fold in the whipped cream gently.
Pile high in pie crust and freeze before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Separate eggs, saving whites.
Beat egg yolks with sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in a small pan.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
In a large flat pan, combine cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Pour butter mixture over cereal, stirring to coat all.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight can.

title: pancit (filipino)
directions: Boil chicken breasts and pork together.
Reserve broth.
Cut into cubes or strips.
Saute garlic, onions and meat in oil.
Add remaining vegetables.
Season with salt and soy sauce.
Put vegetables aside.
Add noodles to broth and cook to medium soft. Add the vegetables and meat and mix.
Do not overcook.
Serve hot. Pancit should not have a lot of liquid when serving.

title: rice pudding
directions: Soak rice for 1/2 hour.
Put milk in pot; add rice and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring constantly.
In separate bowl, add eggs, Carnation milk, sugar and vanilla; beat together.
When rice is cooked, add these ingredients and when it comes to a boil, shut it off.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Excellent.

title: candy
directions: Combine frosting mix, syrup, vanilla and boiling water in bowl.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks about 5 minutes.
Beat at slow speed and blend in powdered sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Drop on waxed paper.
When firm, turn over and allow to dry 12 hours. Store in an airtight container.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, milk, salt and butter.
Cook until thickened.
Pour when cool into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into florets.
Combine dressing of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
One hour before serving, combine dressing with vegetables.
Garnish with raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon.

title: chocolate banana drop
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Mix shortening with next three ingredients until creamy.
Mix in chocolate, then mix in flour mixture alternately with bananas.
Drop by teaspoons 1 1/2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: honey sand balls
directions: In
a
large mixing bowl, beat together butter, the 1/2 cup powdered
sugar
and honey.
Add flour, nuts, vanilla and salt. Mix
thoroughly
using hands, if necessary.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place
inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake
in a 325° oven for 14 to 16 minutes or until the cookies are barely tinged with brown.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine in large bowl all ingredients but chocolate chips.
Beat into creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips and mix just until mixed.
Drop tablespoons about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool and then remove.

title: make ahead company breakfast
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of greased casserole.
Fry sausage; chop into fine pieces and drain.
Beat eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle sausage over bread, then add egg mixture.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
Put in cold oven and set temperature to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in 4 cups water. When potatoes are tender, mix 2 tablespoons flour in 1/2 cup water until thick; add to potatoes. Beat egg and add to potatoes. Add 1 to 2 cups milk; simmer until hot.

title: sister rit's chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix self-rising flour, plain flour, eggs and salt with just enough cold water to make a stiff dough; roll real thin.
Cut in small pieces and drop in chicken broth.
(You can take chicken out and tear off bone; set aside and make dumplings in broth.)
Drop a few in at a time and let cook before you drop any more.
Don't stir dumplings hard.
From top, take spoon and push them down into broth.
Stir from bottom slowly.
When they are done, if gravy is not thick enough, while cooking, sprinkle a little flour over them and push down with a spoon.

title: early american brown bread(no eggs!)
directions: Mix whole wheat flour, white flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Stir milk mixture gradually into flour mixture until well blended.
Spoon batter into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish pudding
directions: Dissolve rennet tablet in water.
Warm milk to tepid.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla together.
Pour warm milk into 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Add egg mixture and stir to mix.
Add dissolved rennet and stir.
Let stand a couple of minutes to set. Bake at 450° until pudding raises up, about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with fruit or whipped cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute butter and onions on stove.
Add Cheddar cheese, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Mix well until all cheese is melted.
Pour over Tater Tots in casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes in 350° oven until done.
Peel and mash potatoes.
Scald milk and add vanilla, sugar and butter.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and orange juice.
Mix well.
Add milk mixture to potatoes.
Put layer of potatoes in casserole.
Add a layer of marshmallows.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Bake at 350° until very hot.
Add top layer of marshmallows and brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart round casserole.
In a bowl mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in raisins with a fork.
Blend in buttermilk and melted margarine until evenly moist.
Put into greased casserole.
Cut an "X" lightly on top.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick put in comes out dry.
Remove from bowl and cool on wire rack.
Makes 16 servings.

title: butter brickle cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients in bowl. Add shortening, milk and vanilla to dry ingredients. Beat with electric mixer on slow to medium speed for 2 minutes. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl frequently. Add egg whites. Beat 2 more minutes, scraping bowl. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: easy beef roast
directions: Dust the roast in the seasoned flour.
Place in a large roasting pan.
Sprinkle the dry soup mix over the roast, then one can of mushroom soup.
Around the edge of the meat, pour the 2nd can of soup and the consomme and the mushrooms.
Seal tightly with foil or lid of roaster.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Slice meat in thin slices.
Serve with gravy over rice, noodles or with mashed potatoes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Pour into greased 1-inch cookie sheet; bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Ice while hot.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt 2/3 stick margarine and mix with onion, salt, pepper, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and hash brown potatoes.
Use a large bowl to mix.
Melt 1/4 cup melted margarine and stir with crushed corn flakes.
Grease
a large 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and place potato mixture in it.
Spoon corn flakes and margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Will have a golden brown top.
Freezes well after baking.

title: gypsy's delight
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add tomato paste, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Mix well. Add corn and put in small, buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top. Place in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cold limas in sour cream
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until thoroughly blended.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add, mixing at low speed until blended.
Add nuts.
Store in 2 rolls in refrigerator or freezer.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Flake the tuna in a mixing bowl.
Add the chopped celery, onion, American cheese and salad dressing.
Spread on split buns and place on a preheated broiling pan.
Broil until the cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add vanilla and pineapple; stir well.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well by hand.
Then add chopped nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks slightly.
Add reserved syrup, sugar, vinegar, salt and butter.
Place over hot (not boiling) water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly and barely coats a spoon (about 12 minutes).
Cool to room temperature.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Combine soup mix, sour cream, bacon, horseradish and mustard. Mix well.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: seafood pizza dip(serve 12 or more)
directions: Soften and spread cream cheese on large serving dish or two smaller dishes.
Spread cocktail sauce over top, leaving a small margin of cream cheese around the edge.
Crumble crab meat and arrange shrimp over sauce.
Place olives and mushrooms on top of seafood layer.
Sprinkle cheese across top.
Arrange crackers around "pizza."

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan over low heat.
Serve warm with Frito chips.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar and butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: glazed whole apricotshouston, texas
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1/2 c. of the juice.
In a large skillet or saucepan, add the apricot juice and all the ingredients above.
Heat slowly at a simmer, turning apricots often until glazed over.
Drain, stick whole cloves in end and use to garnish poultry or pork (Thanksgiving turkey).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°
Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in separate bowl, flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla, beating after each addition.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake 1 1/2 hours.
This cake doesn't need frosting, but the Chocolate Gloss can be added if desired.

title: low-fat taco dip
directions: Mix salsa and refried beans and spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread over beans.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped onion and approximately 1/2 cup fat-free cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix dry mustard, mayonnaise and yellow mustard together; set aside.
Grate cabbage and carrots together.
Sprinkle with salt. Drain excess juices off.
You will have to squeeze the mixture by hand.
Place in a bowl.
Combine grated onion, celery seed, sweet pickle juice, sugar and vinegar; add to mixture of mustard and mayo.
Fold into cabbage.

title: myrtle sizemore's egg custard meringue pie
directions: Beat 6 egg yolks and 2 whole eggs slightly.
Add sugar, flour and cornstarch.
Add hot milk gradually.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour mixture into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375° until firm.
Don't overcook.

title: don's bavarian pot roast
directions: Pour beer over roast and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over roast; continue baking at 350°, covered, until meat is well done.
Use broth to pour over meat when served.

title: forget me not tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight jar.

title: bee's broccoli salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients and refrigerate overnight, (dressing).
Pour the dressing over the other ingredients just before serving.
Serve chilled.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water and juice.
Add fruit.
Chill until set.
Mix pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip.
Top jello mix with the pudding mix and top with chopped pecans.

title: date bars
directions: Cook the dates and water; cool slightly, then add the vanilla. Set this mixture aside.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients. Add the water and oil to dry ingredients.
Use a little more than half on the bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with dates.
Spread the remainder on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: salisbury steak deluxe
directions: In a bowl combine the soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish; blend well.
Set aside.
In another bowl lightly beat the egg.
Add bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper and 1/4 cup of the soup mixture.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water and sugar until syrupy.
Add cranberries and cook until they burst.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Remove cover and cook another 5 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Add fruit, marshmallows and nuts to cooled cranberries and thoroughly chill.

title: barbecue shredded beef
directions: Cook meat until very tender in a small amount of water to which 3 teaspoons salt has been added.
While meat is cooking, make sauce.
Melt shortening and add onion; cook until tender but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Shred beef and add to sauce.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 10 to 12 sandwiches.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with water and orange juice.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: different potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins, peel and slice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Begin with layer of potatoes in casserole.
Spread with dressing mixture and continue alternating, ending with mixture. Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Stir in water and butter, using water at room temperature.
Cook in microwave for about 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
(This will get quite thick.)
Remove from microwave stirring thoroughly.
Blend in vanilla.

title: easy zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a greased 10-inch square casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add to the butter/sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add potato chips and vanilla. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oreo peanut butter crunch squares
directions: Finely crush 20 of the cookies; mix with butter.
Press firmly onto bottom of greased 8 inch square baking pan.
Coarsely chop remaining cookies; set aside.
Drop spoonfuls of marshmallow creme evenly onto crust to within 1/2 inch of outer edges. Sprinkle with chocolate chunks, peanuts and chopped cookies.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until marshmallow creme just begins to brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2 inch squares. Makes 16 servings.

title: low-fat gelatin dessert
directions: Mix jello with Cool Whip that has been defrosted.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Add cottage cheese and refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry pear crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine rice, pears, cranberries, 1/3 cup of the brown sugar and 2 tablespoons of the flour.
Spray a 2-quart baking dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Place rice mixture in bottom; set aside.
Combine remaining flour, remaining sugar and oats in a bowl.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add pecans and coconut; blend well.
Sprinkle over rice mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve warm.
Top with frozen vanilla yogurt, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.
Each serving has 271 calories.

title: play doh
directions: Boil water and salt.
Add salad oil, alum and food coloring. Add flour.
Add flour gradually.
Mix well.
Knead when cool.
Add more flour, if sticky.

title: "oh so easy meat pie"
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine ingredients together; pour into uncooked pie shell.
Place another pie shell on top; press edges down with a fork.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: matt's horseradish sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken strips with garlic powder.
Set aside. Simmer all other ingredients 15 minutes.
Add chicken.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat well eggs, sugar and salt.
Add white syrup, waffle syrup, vanilla and butter to eggs and sugar.
Mix.
Add pecans or more, if desired.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Filling will be raised and brown.

title: griffith's shortbread old frostburg recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Cut in unsoftened butter until it forms small pea size lumps.
Dump ingredients on cool marble slab.
Will still be powder.
Start pounding and working until you form a soft dough, oily to touch.
Form a ball. Roll out on unfloured slab to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into rounds with biscuit cutter.
Lift carefully with cake turner to ungreased cool cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned around bottom edge.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap cookies in wax paper to best preserve buttery taste.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in punch bowl. Chill before serving.

title: peanut butter apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour water and lemon juice over apples. Combine sugar, flour, salt and oatmeal.
Blend in butter and peanut butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Spread evenly over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until crust is crisp and apples are tender.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls and press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: savory salmon luncheon pie
directions: Prick pastry shell with tines of a fork; bake in a 450° oven for 5 minutes. Drain salmon, reserving liquid; remove bones and skin.
Flake salmon and place in bottom of pastry shell; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Saute onions and parsley flakes in butter; sprinkle over salmon.
Mix liquid from salmon with eggs, milk and remaining ingredients; pour over salmon.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes, or until firm.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Add all ingredients into large pot.
Cook good.
Serve over rice.
Add salt and pepper for taste.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: In a skillet over medium high heat in hot oil, cook beef and garlic until meat is brown.
Add onion; cook 5 more minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling point.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to cover.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease the bottom of a Bundt or tube pan.
Add nuts to bottom if desired.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Melt butter, sugar and syrup until sugar melts (can be microwaved).
Pour mixture over rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover tightly with foil and let rise 2 to 3 hours or overnight. Bake covered 1/2 hour at 350°.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before turning onto cake platter.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Slice peaches in bowl.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and set aside.
Mix the first 7 ingredients for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased deep 9-inch pie plate.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup. Place peaches on batter in pie plate.
In separate bowl, mix for 2 minutes the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach juice.
Spoon over batter within 1-inch of plate.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian dressing and vegetables with rice
directions: Put Italian dressing in a skillet; add vegetables.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Can be served over rice.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and water, stirring to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 5-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients. Add milk; mix until well blended.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased bread tins.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: upside-down cherry cobbler
directions: Thoroughly cream together 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add milk, mixing well.
(Don't worry about lumps.)
Spread batter in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Distribute cherries evenly over batter.
Pour on cherry liquid.
Sprinkle cherries with remaining 1/2 cup sugar. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix first seven ingredients and shape into small bite size balls.
Melt the wax and chocolate chips in pan, then dip balls in this mixture and place on wax paper to cool.

title: oreo surprise(desserts)
directions: Crush entire package of Oreos to fine consistency (potato masher works fine for this). Saving out 1/2 c. of Oreo crumbs for later use.
Mix remaining crumbs and melted margarine and press into bottom of 9x13 baking pan.
Push firmly with a spoon or spatula.
Place in refrigerator for 5 minutes.

title: frog in a log
directions: Spray frying pan with Pam; take bread and pinch out the center (just a small hole).
Put bread in skillet.
Drop egg in middle of the bread (where the hole is).
Add salt and pepper; let it brown and turn over.
Eat it hot.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks thoroughly.
Add milk and beat again.
Sift flour with salt and sugar.
Add to egg mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Add butter and let mixture cool, then add vanilla. Mix in shredded coconut.
Turn into baked pie shell.
Cover with stiffly beaten egg whites to which has been added 6 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown in a 300° oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Add all soup
mixture
together
to
make up 32 ounces. Add water to make up the differences.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch saucepan.
Pour
over
rice
evenly
in
pan.
Place chicken in pan on
top of rice.
Pour soup over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: best broccoli soup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add broccoli, celery and carrots; boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
In same kettle, saute onion in oleo until tender.
Stir in flour to form smooth paste.
Gradually add broth and milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil; boil and stir 1 minute.
Add vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: famous broccoli casserole surprise
directions: Cook
broccoli	and rice.
In separate saucepan combine remaining
ingredients;
add
enough
milk to make the mixture pour
like thick soup. In casserole dish, layer rice, broccoli and sauce until dish is full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.

title: pepper steak oriental
directions: Cut meat in 1/2-inch strips, 2 inches long.
Brown meat, garlic, etc., in skillet.
Add tomatoes in center of pan.
Cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch and water; cook until thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion, celery and green pepper in large pan. Drain off fat by spooning.
Add the soup, sauce, water and seasoning.
Simmer 30 minutes with lid ajar.
Add beans when chili is done; heat through.
Thin with water if needed.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Take center and seed out of peppers.
Drop into boiling water; let stand 5 minutes without boiling.
Fry onions in margarine until golden brown.
Add hamburger and garlic; stir with a fork. Cook and drain rice.
Add rice to meat; let cool.
Put mixture into peppers; cover with tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Heat until hot.
Pour into 6 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onions on top, followed by olives and finally the cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Serve with Doritos or other taco-style chips.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save 1 cup broth.
Cut up meat and mix with 1 can soup and sour cream.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and top with the Stove Top mixed with 1 cup broth and melted stick of margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then debone.
Cut up chicken and put in casserole.
Combine soup and broth and pour over chicken.

title: grandma's fruit cake recipe
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add eggs to this mixture, then other wet ingredients (milk, lemon juice and vanilla).
Sift flour, cinnamon, cloves, mace, baking powder and soda together and set aside. Cut up pecans, orange peel, pineapple, citron, cherries, almonds, raisins and currants in a large bowl.
Cover pans with waxed paper (Bundt or angel food pans) and spray where you can't cover.
Heat oven to 300°.
Combine the dry mixture with the wet mixture, then include it with the cut up fruits and nuts. Thoroughly mix together and pour into pans and bake for 4 hours, very slow.

title: double baked potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Bake potatoes until tender; let cool. Scoop out pulp leaving about 1/4-inch in shell.
Mash pulp in large mixing bowl with crumbled bacon and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put back into shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave for 5 minutes until heated through and serve.
(These can be done in the morning and then re-heated.)

title: super bowl pizza
directions: Toast muffins in oven.
Take the muffins out of the oven and top with spaghetti sauce.
Then top with pepperoni and olives. Top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven.
Enjoy.

title: cheese sauce for baked potatoes
directions: Blend flour in melted butter; make a thick and smooth cream sauce by adding milk gradually and stirring constantly.
Season with Worcestershire, Tabasco and salt.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Add onions or top potatoes with onions before pouring sauce over.
A different way to serve baked potato and one men especially enjoy.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix onion and cabbage and set aside.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and add to cabbage and onions.
Marinate for 15 minutes or more.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate egg whites from yolks.
Mix yolks with Eagle Brand. Squeeze juice from lemons.
Mix with Eagle Brand and yolks.
Pour into pie crust.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: appetizer spareribs
directions: Have sparerib racks cut into 3-inch lengthwise strips.
Cut strips into individual ribs.
Place in a shallow baking pan. Blend together molasses and mustard.
Stir in lemon juice, soy sauce, Worcestershire and cayenne.
Mix well.
Brush spareribs with part of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, brushing often with remaining sauce.
Drain on paper towels.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Heat 3 teaspoons oil in skillet.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Remove onion and set aside.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl. Add onion, spinach, cheese and seasonings.
Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in same skillet; add egg mixture.
Cook 5 minutes or until browned lightly.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange dried beef in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wrap a piece of bacon around each chicken breast.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, onion soup mix and sour cream.
Spread over chicken breasts. Cover and bake 1 hour at 275°.
Uncover and bake 2 more hours.

title: marie's black bean soup
directions: First, soak beans overnight.
Boil with full quart of hot water.
Fry chopped onion, garlic, chopped green pepper and bacon. Add to beans; salt and pepper to taste.
Do not salt until tender.
Add mixture to beans, which should have some liquid, and let simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Remove fat from chicken backs and boil backs with onions, celery and Herb-Ox broth for 30 minutes.
Combine string beans, carrots, limas and tomato paste.
Cook 20 minutes (until vegetables are tender).
Add okra, potato, corn and macaroni.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for about 1 hour.
Bottle and keep refrigerated.

title: red mush
directions: Boil.
Add 2 small packages strawberry jello and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: honey sugared pecans
directions: Toast pecans in moderate oven (350°) 10 minutes, stirring once.
Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, water, honey, salt and cinnamon.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°), without stirring.
Remove from heat; beat until mixture begins to get creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir gently until nuts are well coated and mixture becomes thick.
Turn out on buttered baking sheet.
With 2 forks, separate nuts at once.

title: deliciously easy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions with following modifications:
Add flour to dry mix and blend well. Substitute equal amount of applesauce for vegetable oil and equal number of egg whites for whole eggs.
Bake in pan of your choice sprayed with cooking spray.
Frost if desired.
Low calorie; low fat.

title: cheese and shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Serve with different kinds of small crackers.

title: bac-on-ion cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 10 inch skillet. Bake for about 20 minutes or until golden brown on top. Remove from skillet immediately.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix all together with concern.
Bake in oven of forgiveness for 2 prayer hours, then cool on table of understanding and serve with compassion.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Squeeze chopped onions, pickles and parsley in a cloth to eliminate excess juices. Stir all the materials together.

title: grape ambrosia
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour into an 8-inch cake pan; chill until firm.

title: cheesy baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beans, chili sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart rectangular baking dish. Arrange onion slices on top.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: beef balls in onion cream
directions: Cook onions in oil until tender but not brown.
Add meat balls and brown on all sides.
Pour off fat, then stir in soup.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally 30 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll into balls and flatten with fork after mixing.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside. In a large mixing bowl, combine shredded cheese, chicken soup, sour cream, chopped onion, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Fold in thawed hash brown potatoes. Turn mixture into prepared baking dish. Toss together corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted butter. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until casserole is golden brown and potatoes are tender.
tags: frozen loose pack hash brown potatoes

title: fat-free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove bones; cut into bite size pieces and return to broth.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add enough milk to make dough as for biscuits.
Roll out to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in strips, then into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Drop a few at a time into boiling broth.
Stir gently occasionally as dumplings are being added.
Lower heat.
Cover.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow to set 2 hours.
Broth will thicken.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Put on medium heat; cook until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat. Cool for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together white sugar and Karo syrup.
Micro on High for 5 minutes.
Take out and add peanuts, micro for 4 more minutes. Take out and add oleo, vanilla, soda and salt.
Stir and pour on greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break.

title: country fried steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak. Roll steak in flour.
Melt margarine in skillet until very hot-brown steak in margarine.
Place in 3 quart baking dish, Make gravy in skillet with 1 can mushroom soup, 3 1/2 cans cold water and onion.
Mix well until hot.
Pour over steak. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350 degree oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm in center.

title: easy fudge
directions: Heat the two ingredients until blended and smooth.
Put into 9 x 13 pan. Cool, then cut into pieces.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and place in mixing bowl.
Melt margarine and pour in potatoes.
Mix well.
Put other ingredients into mixture and mix well.
Pour into 2 small unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 200° until done.

title: delicious coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Cook 2 minutes longer, then add 1 cup coconut. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Take egg whites and beat well.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar; beat 2 minutes longer.
Cover with meringue.
Add coconut on top of meringue.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cinnamon pancakes(serving for 4 to 6 people)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, ground cinnamon and sugar into a mixing bowl.
Beat together egg yolks and milk.
Add vegetable oil, while mixing, then add all at once to dry ingredients; stir just until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.

title: crispy cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, green pepper, onion, carrot and red pepper.
Mix vinegar solution real well and pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well and seal in a Tupperware bowl.
Serve after 24 hours.
Keep one month in refrigerator or freeze.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into bowl; add 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
In bowl, cream shortening, sugar and salt thoroughly.
Blend in mashed potatoes; blend in eggs.
Add the remaining lukewarm water.
Add most of sifted flour gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Add maybe 1/2 cup more flour to take stickiness from dough.
Knead on lightly floured board.
Round up and set dough to rise in greased bowl. Cover with damp cloth.
Keep dough at 80° to 85° until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Punch down; make up desired amount of dough by letting it rise again, double in bulk, about 45 minutes.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Whip together the berries, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and salt for 15 minutes with electric mixer.
Whip the cream; add vanilla and fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Freeze.
Top with additional berries to serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll out like biscuits (except thinner) and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat margarine on high until creamy.
Add sugar 1 cup at a time on
high.
Add eggs 1 at a time on high; beat well.
Add flour
and
alternate
with cream as from the container (do not whip).
Just
add
to
flour
and beat well.
Use a greased and floured
tube
pan.
Place
in
COLD oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: buffalo style chicken pizza
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces (1/4 to 1/2 inch).
Thoroughly cook in frying pan.
Add barbecue sauce and vinegar; add Red Hot to taste.
Prepare your favorite pizza crust (I buy premade dough from Wegmans).
Spread Blue cheese dressing on crust to coat.
Spread chicken and sauce over crust.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Add chopped celery to top and baked until crust is golden brown.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and put in a microwave safe bowl.
Add rotel. Then add bacon bits.
Melt on high 5 minutes, take out and stir. Reheat for 5 more minutes, take out and stir.
Keep heating and stirring until melted.
Serve with Bite size tortillia chips.

title: chicken and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees.
Can be made ahead of time and heated at time of serving.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream
margarine
and
shortening;
add
sugar and beat until smooth.
Add
egg
yolks, one at a time, and continue to beat. Combine
flour and soda;
add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat sweet potatoes in saucepan.
Mash.
Combine sugar, margarine, pineapple and cinnamon and add to sweet potatoes.
Pour into baking dish and cover with miniature marshmallows.
Heat until marshmallows are light brown.
Serve warm.

title: finger gelatin
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water or juice.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, chocolate, margarine, evaporated milk and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until it bubbles.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Take off heat.
Stir in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop with spoon onto wax paper.

title: sausage yummy
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. Mix thoroughly with cream cheese. Spread one package crescent rolls to make bottom crust and place in a 9 x 11-inch greased baking pan. Spread meat mixture on top of unbaked crust. Spread the other package of rolls on top to make crust.
Pinch crusts together around edges.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown, about 10 minutes. Cool and cut into squares. May be frozen before baking.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes well.
Squeeze out all the juices.
Break artichokes into small pieces; add mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix well.
Add garlic powder, salt and lemon juice and mix lightly. Place in shallow baking dish (quiche pan).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Remove from oven; blot top with paper towels.
Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 8.

title: best ever sweet potatoes
directions: Boil until thickened.
Place sweet potatoes in a buttered dish and top with the remaining ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Top with marshmallows and return to the oven to melt.

title: corn relish
directions: If fresh corn is used, boil corn for 5 minutes.
Dip in cold water.
Cut from cob and measure.
Combine all ingredients and boil gently for 20 minutes.
Pack while boiling into hot sterilized jars.
Be sure vinegar solution covers all vegetables.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into small pieces and line bottom of punch bowl with cake.
Pour some pudding over cake, then some cherry pie filling, pineapple, sliced bananas and then Cool Whip.
Start layering again until punch bowl is full.
(Goes a long way.)

title: "chiffon dream"
directions: Blend at low speed the lemon Jell-O, 1 tablespoon sugar and 3/4 cup water until dissolved.
Add 1 cup ice and stir by hand until partially dissolved.
Add 4 ounces cream cheese and blend at high speed until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into pie crust. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Swirl into lemon mixture until pie crust is full.
Pour remainder into a bowl.
Chill until set; spread with Cool Whip.

title: winter wonder log
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Blend in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread mixture on wafers.
Stack in groups of 8 or 10.
On plastic wrap, place stacks together on sides to form the log.
Wrap and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Unwrap and frost with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish; slice diagonally.
Serves 8.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: In a large bowl on low speed, combine first 10 ingredients. Mix 2 to 3 minutes.
Mixture will be heavy.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Top with whipped cream when served.
I used red Roman apples.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, drain fat.
Add next seven ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to directions. Serve with grated Romano cheese.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients on large round plate.
Serve with tortilla strips.

title: peaches 'n cream cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix 2 minutes.
Pour into 8-inch greased pie dish.
Drain peaches; save the liquid.
Arrange peaches over batter.
Combine the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons peach juice.
Beat for 2 minutes; spread over peaches. Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: breaded pineapple
directions: Mix all together (if too dry, add 1/2 cup milk).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and peanut butter.
Roll into balls and chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into mixture with toothpicks.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter; let cool completely.
Mix with other ingredients. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter; add eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients and add nuts.
Make 2 rolls and wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/8-inch thick and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy clam chowder
directions: Saute onion until tender.
Add in flour, then pepper, wine, potato and clams. Cook until thickens.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat. Add cream. Return to heat.
Be careful not to boil.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix spices together and sprinkle over apples; melt margarine. Mix with 3/4 cup water.
Pour over apples.
Pour apple mixture into pie crust.
Cover with top crust and bake at 350° until apples are tender and crust is brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and bouillon with onion and water to cover chicken.
When done, take chicken out.
Mix 1/4 cup flour and about 1/2 cup water in a shaker.
Mixture should be a smooth consistency. Bring broth back to a boil.
Slowly add flour mixture until gravy thickens.
Break chicken apart; put in casserole dish.
Pour gravy over chicken.
Place in oven at 350° until gravy is simmering. While waiting, mix Bisquick and water, forming a dough mixture. Roll and flatten to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits; place in casserole.
Bake until brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Wash broccoli, removing tough ends.
Peel stems if tough. Split broccoli into separate flowerets.
Cut pieces so they are no more than 3 inches long.
Put broccoli into steamer basket.
Steam for approximately 10 minutes or until broccoli is bright green, but still tender-crisp in texture.
Remove onto heated serving dish.
Cover.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler or microwave for 1 minute.
Melt and stir.
Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat yolks; add salt, almond extract and vanilla.
Stir again.
Whip heavy cream until stiff; set aside. Blend everything to egg yolks.
Add everything to egg whites.
Add chocolate, egg whites and heavy cream.
Fold carefully.
Pour into another serving bowl.
Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: crazy bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. michigan meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Place in baking dish and pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) and 1 small can mushroom pieces (drained) or you can use tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pineapple layer cake
directions: Mix and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: jackie's potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes with celery, onions and garlic in 2 1/2 cups water. When potatoes are tender, add margarine, cheese and milk. Mash with potato masher until creamy. Salt and pepper to taste. Top with crumbled, fried bacon.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Coat the chicken in a mixture of the flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine eggs and milk.
Dip coated chicken in this and then roll it in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place chicken, bone side down, in baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
(Also butter bottom of pan.)
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Lightly beat eggs, milk and sugar.
Add cans of corn and mix together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with crushed saltines.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until center is set, or microwave for 10 minutes, or until center is set.

title: french bread braids
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups of flour, salt, sugar and dry yeast.
Add shortening and warm water.
Blend at lowest speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn out on well-floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough; divide in half.
Divide each half into three parts.
Form each part into a strip 14 inches long.
Braid the three together, sealing ends. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Repeat with other half.
Brush with mixture of egg white and water.
Cover loosely and let rise until light and doubled in size, about 45 minutes.
Brush again with egg white mixture.
Poppy or sesame seed can be sprinkled on.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: baked salmon
directions: Drain salmon; flake in large pieces.
Arrange in bottom of medium sized shallow casserole.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Spread over salmon and bake in a moderate oven at 400° about 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in peelings until done.
Peel potatoes while they are still warm, then let potatoes cool and cube them.
Mix in all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Lightly grease baking sheet. Put the flour into a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center. Add the lard and buttermilk.
Start working the flour into the milk and lard, squeezing the mixture through the fingers until a soft dough is formed.
This will be a sticky dough.
Lift the dough from the bowl and place on a well-floured surface.
Sprinkle a little flour on top of the dough and start folding, gently kneading and turning the dough until it is no longer sticky.
Pat the dough to a thickness of about 1/2 inch.
Cut with a 2 inch cutter. Place on the baking sheet. If a crispy outside is desired, the biscuits are placed about an inch apart.
For a soft biscuit, place with the edges touching.
Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Best served hot from the oven.
Yield: 8 to 10 biscuits.

title: shrimp platter dip
directions: Use a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, catsup and cocktail sauce.
Spread over platter, then pour cocktail sauce, next shrimp.
Sprinkle Mozzarella.
Next, layer chopped tomato, pepper and onion.
Chill.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Beat cream cheese and marshmallow creme together until blended well.
Add vanilla.
If too thick, add small amount of milk.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, saute the onion and pepper in the butter.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and oregano.
Add ground beef.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Place 1/2 of the spaghetti in a greased 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish.
Top with half of the mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 c. shredded cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix the soup and water until smooth.
Pour over the casserole.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook your rice, then cook your broccoli.
Mix rice, broccoli, can of Ro-Tel, cheese and onion in casserole dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of casserole.
Cook in microwave 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate chicken wings 3 days, turning periodically.
Layer wings in pan; pour a little marinade juice over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, turning wings over every 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix butter with cracker crumbs; reserve 1/2 cup.
Mix remaining crumbs with broccoli, corn and seasonings. Turn into a buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup butter crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: jello pie
directions: Put all ingredients except milk and lemon juice in a pot and bring to a boil, stirring often.
Cool completely.

title: country chicken with onion biscuits
directions: Combine chicken, bacon, mixed vegetables, tomatoes and 1 cup cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend soup and milk in bowl. Pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Drop Onion Biscuit Dough by spoonfuls into 12 biscuits on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Top with French fried onions and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield:
6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff sandwich
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Add salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cut bread lengthwise in half; butter both halves.
Place on baking sheet.
Remove meat mixture; stir in sour cream.
Spoon onto bread.
Sprinkle with tomatoes, green pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted, about 20 minutes.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on the box.
Fill the cones about 1/2 to 3/4 full with batter.
Bake on a cookie sheet, using the temperature and length of time indicated for cupcakes.
Let the cones cool, then frost and add jimmies to frosting.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: cottage cheese luncheon salad
directions: Season cottage cheese with salt and pepper.
If very moist, drain.
Add radishes, chives and mayonnaise.
If too dry, moisten with a little cream or extra mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Boil peeled potatoes until done.
Mix water, soup and gravy.
Put layer of beef, layer of mixed vegetables, layer of potatoes and 1/2 soup and gravy mixture.
Do this again, ending with gravy mixture on top.
Bake at 500° until it simmers.

title: old-fashioned southern chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix cornbread, celery, onion and seasonings.
Add well beaten egg and butter; mix thoroughly.
Moisten with hot chicken broth until soft.
Pour into a well-greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or use to stuff a 10 to 14 pound turkey.

title: hash brown cheddar bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine hash browns, sour cream, chicken soup, Cheddar cheese, onion, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Place mixture in a large baking pan. Combine crushed cornflakes and margarine. Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Wonderful dish to serve with barbecue steaks or London broil.

title: banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a jellyroll pan.
Mix Spry, sugar, eggs, bananas and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend dry ingredients into banana mixture.
Spread into pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add milk, melted margarine and vanilla.
Put coconut in unbaked crust and pour filling over coconut.
(When you put the filling over the coconut, the coconut seems to go through the pie better.)
Bake at 350° until browned, but still a little shaky.

title: homemade finger paint
directions: Add starch to water.
Stir over heat until thick.
Add detergent and stir well.
Divide into small jars.
Color with tempera paint or food coloring.
Keeps in refrigerator.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain and add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and vegetables.
Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: italian corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 3 qt. casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Boil zucchini and water for 6 minutes, then drain.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Add jello; bring back to boil.
Pour mixture into hot jars and seal.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix water and 100% bran and let stand.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs (1 at a time).
Add All-Bran and buttermilk.
Combine all of the ingredients and mix only until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins (2/3 full). Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter may be covered and refrigerated for up to 6 weeks.
Recipe may also be halved.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish with margarine.
Place apples in bottom of casserole and sprinkle lightly with few drops of lemon juice.
Spread cranberries over this and sprinkle sugar over top.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: In a 9 x 13 baking dish, sprayed with cooking spray, layer 1 can crescent rolls (pinch together seams). Mix cream cheese and cup of sugar for middle layer. Layer other can of crescent rolls. Bake at 350° until rolls begin turning brown. Mix together milk and powdered sugar; drizzle on top while warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Pour batter into well greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven and set temperature at 325°
and bake an hour and 20 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool 15 or 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: broccoli and cheese tart
directions: Take a 9-inch pie crust; bake and remove from oven.
Brush with Dijon mustard.
Meanwhile, cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and chop.
Mix with cream, eggs, salt, cayenne, nutmeg and cheese. Pour into prepared crust.
Sprinkle around edges of top with sunflower seeds, if desired.
Bake at 370° for 35 minutes or until set.
Serve hot, warm or at room temperature.

title: tex-mex layered dip(serves 12)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Separately, mix next 3 ingredients. Layer jalapeno bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, green onions, tomatoes and olives (mixed together) and cheese.

title: chicken taco soup
directions: Boil chicken until done. After it cools, shred with fork. In large saucepan, combine olive oil, taco seasoning, onion, garlic and chicken. Cook until onions are clear. Combine all ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated. Serve in individual bowls with corn chips and top with shredded cheese.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Do not drain fruit cocktail.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Before putting in oven, mix together nuts, brown sugar and coconut; sprinkle over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese and egg sandwiches
directions: Cut sandwiches into small triangles or into fancy shapes with cookie cutters or make open faces and cut in fancy shapes.

title: tammy's potatoes
directions: Wash and cube unpeeled potatoes; place in frying pan. Add the remaining ingredients; cover and cook over medium heat, stirring often. When potatoes are tender, remove cover and cook until water is cooked out.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt butter and chocolate with the coffee.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Beat chocolate mixture and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
On low speed beat in dry ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours. Grease cookie sheets.
Roll teaspoonful of cookie dough into the confectioners sugar after forming ball with cookie dough.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° or until tops are just set.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool on sheets for 1 minute, then transfer to racks until completely cooled.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: picnic cake
directions: Beat eggs stiff and add sugar gradually.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: emporium chili
directions: Lightly brown onions and meat; break up meat in small pieces. Add puree and everything except kidney beans.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add beans; cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: party mix
directions: Put the first six ingredients into a roasting pan and mix with hands.
Mix together the oil, butter, Worcestershire sauce and salts in a saucepan; heat, but do not boil.
Then pour over the other mixture.
Stir well.
Bake, covered, in 200° oven for 2 hours and 10 minutes, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: hot pinto beans
directions: Wash beans well and place in large saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Add salt pork, salt, pepper, onion, peppers and chili powder.
Cook on medium heat until beans are tender or cooking time of about 3 or 4 hours and adding water when needed.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute mushrooms in their juice in a heavy skillet. Add oregano, rice and butter. Chop finely and add ALL of green onions including the top green part. Into a large casserole, put beef consomme and hot water. Add all other ingredients and bake approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour at 450°. When it is finished, all the liquid will be absorbed.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings in a large skillet over moderate heat for 10 minutes, or until onion is golden.
Add beef and saute, breaking meat up with a spoon about ten minutes until lightly browned, drain off fat as it accumulates.

title: cherry swirl coffee cake
directions: In bowl, blend sugar, eggs, butter, shortening, baking powder and extracts on low speed.
Increase to high speed and whip for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Spread 2/3 batter over bottom of greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, greased.
Spread pie filing over batter in pan.
Drop remaining tablespoons over all. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden.
While baking, prepare a glaze of 1 cup confectioners sugar and 1 or 2 tablespoons milk.
Drizzle over cake while warm.
Is best when served immediately.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Mix soup, water and rice.
Place in a buttered casserole dish, salt and pepper fryer pieces and place on top of rice mixture.
Place cover on dish and bake 1 1/2 hours or until fryer is tender.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (or 325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: cabbage stir-fry
directions: Finely chop pepper, green onion tops and dark green leaves from cabbage.
Cook in Dutch oven with 2 tablespoons bacon drippings and 1/2 cup water.
Cook until tender.
Chop remaining white cabbage and onions; add to pot.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add tad of water, if needed.

title: canopies
directions: Mix all together (can make ahead) and put on bread.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in airtight sealed container.
Mix about 4 teaspoons of drink mix with boiling water in a cup.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: rose's fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, water and lemon juice in small saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool completely.
Combine fruit in salad bowl.
Add lemon mixture; mix gently.
Chill for several hours to overnight.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake about 30 minutes or until set and browned.
Bake at 350°.

title: our favorite cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Add pie filling to top of pie.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and the vanilla.
Stir in flour, nuts and salt until dough holds together; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set but not brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm; cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: turkey cordon bleu
directions: Combine broccoli, water and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in stuffing mix.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, place turkey slices in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover each with a slice of ham and then a slice of cheese.
Spoon broccoli stuffing over cheese.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Meanwhile, heat gravy and serve with turkey.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: mexican pan bread
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in oven-proof skillet.
Leave half of sauteed mix in unheated skillet and put other half in medium bowl with chili powder, cumin, green pepper, salt, cooked beans and stock, egg, cornmeal and baking powder.
Mix well and pour into skillet over onion mixture.
