Do not stir so that onion will stay on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk hot cakes
directions: Mix well and cook on hot griddle.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Slice onion.
Finely chop garlic.
In a large skillet, heat butter and oil over moderate heat.
Add the onion and saute until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add the garlic and saute for 2 more minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and make into a ball.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix and bake in same plate.
Sift flour and salt in pie plate. Boil shortening and water.
Add hot mixture to flour.
Mix with fork until all flour is moist.
Work with hands and pat into shape.
Flute edges.
Prick with fork and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes one (8-inch) pie shell.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Place over heat; stir until it reaches a boil, then boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered pans. Let stand overnight before cutting.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: spinach new orleans
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Drain.
Add cream cheese, onion, 1/2 stick butter, nutmeg and salt to taste.
Place in casserole. Cover with Pepperidge Farm dressing. Pour 1/2 stick butter, melted, over dressing.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
(If dough seems dry, work with hands.)
Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each olive.
Shape into ball. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Chill at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, cream cheese, salt, pepper, egg and flour.
Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Put onion rings on top when ready to bake.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and salt in top of double boiler; blend. Add gelatin.
Place over boiling water; beat constantly with rotary beater until thick and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Cool, place peanut butter in bowl; add remaining 1/2 cup water gradually, beat until smooth.
Add vanilla to egg yolk mixture; blend.
Chill until slightly thickened, but still syrupy, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add remaining 1/4 cup sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Fold into peanut butter mixture. Turn into crumb crust.
(You may use baked pastry shell.) Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: near east barbecued beef
directions: Remove all fat from meat.
In a bowl, combine the onion, garlic, soy sauce, sugar, pepper and oil.
Pour mixture over the strips of beef and coat well with your hands.
Broil the marinated meat, turning once, until tender (about 5 minutes on each side).

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add green pepper and onion until tender.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.

title: hearty vegetable barley soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, brown meat in oil.
Add onion and garlic and continue cooking until onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except green beans.
Cover, bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add green beans and continue cooking 10 minutes or until meat and barley are tender.
Additional water may be added if soup becomes too thick.
Makes twelve 1-cup servings.

title: crunchy asian snow peas
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil (approx. 5 quarts). When water begins to boil, add snow peas just until color changes, about 15-30 seconds. Immediately drain into colander and rinse well with cold tap water. Snow peas should be crisp and a beautiful green color. In a large bowl, combine oyster sauce, soy sauce and sesame oil. Add snow peas to mixture and toss well to coat. Add chopped scallions. Refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: cottage cheese cookies
directions: Mix all together very well.
Roll out on floured board very thin.
Cut in squares, 2 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Fill each square with your favorite Solo fillings.
Fold in triangle; place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, 3 tablespoons steak sauce, egg, bread crumbs, garlic and salt.
Form into 24 meatballs.
In a large skillet, brown meatballs well in oil and then drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water.
Stir in mixture.
Add green pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Stir together oats, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat dough in bottom
and up sides of a quiche dish or 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounding measuring tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 or 10 minutes. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields 5 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: poppy's toll house cupcakes
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, vanilla and granulated sugar; beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Spoon by rounded tablespoonfuls into paper-lined 2 1/2-inch cupcake cups.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
When thoroughly cooked, shred meat.
Discard bones and skin.
In medium saucepan saute onion in margarine.
Add chicken, soups, chili or salsa and heat through.
In large glass baking dish, layer tortilla chips, chicken mixture and then cheese. Repeat layers.
Put in 350° oven and bake until top is slightly boiling and brown.

title: noonies icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add egg, then flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add the nuts and cinnamon.
Roll in a long roll; wrap in wax paper.
Set in icebox for 12 hours.
When cold, slice and put on cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Roll ingredients into a ball and chill.
Serve with cocktail sauce over it.
Use any kind of crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, margarine, flour and bananas. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli rice au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Blend
all
ingredients together.
Add milk up to "full line" of ice cream freezer.
Serves 10.

title: fried stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Split peppers; clean out all seeds.
Fill the 2 halves with softened cream cheese and freeze.
When frozen, dip in batter and deep fry.
These are delicious!
Use any batter recipe or buy a prepackaged mix.

title: eggplant balls
directions: Peel and cut eggplant.	Place in boiling water and cook for 1/2
hour or until soft.
Drain in colander for 1/2 hour. Combine all
ingredients
except
sauce and peppers.
Mix and shape into balls.
Place in heated frying pan with oil and fry until slightly
brown.
Place
on
flat
baking
sheet.
Fry peppers and place on eggplant balls, scattering over top.
Add sauce to top of peppers; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in preheated oven. Makes
balls.
After
frying
place in sauce instead of meatballs.

title: low-fat apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray bottom of 12 medium muffin cups with vegetable spray.
In a large bowl, beat milk, yogurt, egg whites, whole egg, vanilla and lemon zest.

title: my mom's goulash
directions: Cook hamburg in water until done, then brown.
Add tomatoes; cook 10 minutes.
Then add macaroni.
Cook 8 minutes, long enough for macaroni to cook.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice, salt and pepper in large bowl; blend well.
Add potatoes, eggs, apple, ham, cucumber and onions; toss gently to mix.

title: 1-2-3 fudge sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan on low heat, stirring constantly with a wire whist.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth. Great for ice cream!

title: puddin'wich
directions: Combine yogurt and peanut butter.
Spread onto graham crackers or cookies.
Top with another cracker.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Freeze.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place sausage; drain.
Separate crescent rolls and place on 12-inch pizza pan (points towards center).
Press over bottom and up sides; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: a cup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into prepared cake pan. Bake at 400° until golden bubbly.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white very stiff.
Add sugar and salt; add pecans. Coat well.
Place 2 tablespoons butter on cookie sheet; melt and spread around.
Place coated nuts on sheet.
Place in oven at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Watch carefully; turn over once.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crackers over top. Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef.
Add tomatoes, sauce and seasonings.
Let simmer. Cook macaroni until done.
Then add macaroni and cheese to sauce. When cheese is melted, dinner is ready.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix Ranch dip, sour cream and cream cheese.
Refrigerate. Spread chilled sour cream mixture onto tortillas.
Sprinkle with parsley, olives and peppers.
Tightly roll tortilla; wrap in foil. Refrigerate for a day.
Unwrap and cut into pinwheels.
Place on serving plate garnished with fresh parsley or lettuce leaves.

title: popover chicken tarragon
directions: Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons of the cooking oil; season with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In bowl, beat eggs; add milk and the remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir together the flour, tarragon and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet and stir until dissolved.
Add bananas, mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart ring mold.
Chill until set.

title: two egg hot water sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar, beating until light.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to egg mixture. Mix well.
Add 1/4 cup boiling water, a little at a time, then add the remaining 1/4 cup boiling water (all at once) and the flavoring.

title: honey dressing for fruit
directions: Add the lemon juice to the honey. Stir in the well beaten eggs.
Mix together thoroughly. Cook over simmering water until thickened.
Mixture will become clear, stirring constantly. Cool. Fold in the whipped cream.
Serve with an assortment of fruit.

title: supreme chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender and chop into bite size pieces.
Crush crackers.
Place half of crushed crackers in bottom of baking dish.
Mix chopped chicken together with water chestnuts, soups and sour cream.
Pour into baking dish, 9 x 9-inch.
Cover with remaining crackers and sliced butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: almond butter cookies(yields 475 to 500 cookies)
directions: Mix almond butter, butter and sugars until well blended.
Add eggs, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour and vanilla. Roll dough out into logs and cut into 1-inch slices.
Put on cookie sheets, ungreased, and press down, but not flat.
Dough should be of a consistency that you can be able to roll into a log.
If of softer consistency, add more flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Beat together sugar, margarine, egg, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add soup with water and soda.
Add flour.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° in a greased and floured loaf pan for approximately 1 hour.

title: joann's cheese potatoes
directions: Fry potatoes until golden brown.
Fry bacon until crispy. Crumble bacon into small bowl, then pour over top of fried potatoes.
Cut cheese into small cubes and pour over top of potatoes and bacon.
Cover and place in microwave until cheese melts.
Cool for 3 minutes, then dip fries into Ranch dressing.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and chicken.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then in crumb mixture, coating well. Arrange pieces in shallow roasting pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Do not turn chicken.

title: cherry supreme pie
directions: Mix lemon juice into condensed milk; stir until thick.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Fold in whipped topping.
Put filling into crusts, mounding up filling on sides.
Spread cherry pie filling on top of pies, but do not spread all the way to the sides.
Chill and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage until done, breaking meat into small pieces as it cooks.
Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add milk, salt and mustard.

title: never fail dill pickles
directions: Fill jars with cucumber spears.
Put powdered alum on top with dill seed and crushed garlic.
Mix and boil the water, vinegar and salt.
Pour hot liquid over pickles.
Screw lid on tight, no need to process.
Good to eat in a few days.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together soda, salt and flour; add to egg mixture.
Add apples, walnuts, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Using juice, heat and mix with Jell-O. Cool.
Whip the whipping cream and cream cheese.
Fold in with the other ingredients, adding pineapple.
Pour into salad mold.
Chill until set.

title: cherry dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside until needed.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken into beaten eggs and roll into bread crumbs.
Melt butter in frypan and brown chicken on both sides.
(Do not try to cook done, just brown.)
Put browned chicken into casserole dish; pour Ragu sauce over chicken. Cover with grated Mozzarella cheese evenly.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese when removed from oven.
Serve hot.

title: gumbo
directions: Heat bacon drippings in skillet over medium heat.
Stir in onion and celery until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir like gravy until mixture is like paste.
Remove from heat and combine all other ingredients in large pot.
Stir in onion mixture.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except zucchini, thoroughly then fold in the zucchini.
Pour into greased pan and bake 30 minutes until brown. Cut into 2-inch squares; serve warm.
Also delicious refrigerator cold.

title: southern corn meal dumplings
directions: Mix flour and
meal
and work in Crisco like pie dough. Add eggs to milk
and
add
to
flour.
Add
more
milk if not enough to handle.
Roll
out and cut in 1-inch pieces and drop in chicken broth
that
is
boiling.
When you add last dough, cover and turn fire out.

title: eggs and cheese
directions: Place eggs, cheese, salt and pepper in a covered jar and shake well.
Heat butter in skillet until melted over medium heat.
Coat skillet with butter.
Pour egg-cheese mixture into hot skillet. Cook over medium heat without stirring.
Turn with spatula when eggs begin to firm on bottom.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until eggs are firm.
Serve warm.

title: microwave chex party mix
directions: Add oleo, Worcestershire and seasoned salt in a small bowl and mix.
Pour cereal, nuts and braids into plastic bag, add oleo mixture and shake until thoroughly mixed.

title: mint-chocolate malted
directions: Place chocolate pieces in saucepan; add 1 cup of the milk. Heat and stir over low heat until chocolate pieces melt.
Stir in remaining milk, malted milk powder, vanilla and mint extract; heat through.
Beat with rotary beater until frothy; pour into cups or mugs.
Serves 6.

title: ziti bake
directions: Prepare spaghetti sauce.
Meanwhile, in 8-quart Dutch oven, prepare ziti macaroni as label directs; drain.
Set aside.

title: percolator punch
directions: Mix and pour into 30 cup percolator.
In top of percolator, put 4 1/2 teaspoons whole cloves and 4 sticks cinnamon.
Perk!

title: enchilada bake(microwave)
directions: Crumble beef in a shallow casserole dish (2 1/2-quart). Sprinkle with minced onion and garlic.
Heat uncovered on Medium-high for approximately 6 minutes.
Stop to stir occasionally to break up meat.
Drain fat.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cut broccoli in pieces.
Place all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour. Stir once or twice during cooking.
Add more milk if casserole appears dry.

title: norwegian pound kake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until grimy.
Mix baking powder with the flour.
Add eggs and flour alternately, then add vanilla. Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: cheese bread
directions: Thaw bread completely.
Slice lengthwise in approximately 7 slices.
Dip each slice in butter, then cheese.
Arrange bread slices around greased angel food cake pan.
Let rise.
Bake 25 minutes until golden brown at 350°.

title: cherry squares
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Combine first four ingredients; mix well.
Blend in flour.
Spread evenly over jelly roll pan. Mark lightly
into
squares.
Drop pie filling into center of each square.
Bake
until
lightly
brown,
25 to 30 minutes. Cool. Sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Peel and slice potatoes and onions in thin slices.
Layer meat, potatoes and onions in a casserole.
Mix soup, salt and pepper; pour over the other ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
In 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 the onion, 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 the crackers.
Repeat layers.
Casserole can be refrigerated at this point and baked later.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon, in a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with uncooked bacon.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.
Delicious.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg and orange juice all at once; fold in nuts and cranberries.
Grease pan well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all together. Pat into squares 1/2 thick. Cut with knife. Place 3-inches apart on pan (closer to be soft). Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot spicy chicken
directions: Mix 2 teaspoons soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and salt. Marinate chicken at least 1 hour, the longer, the better.
Mix remaining soy sauce, sherry, vinegar, chicken broth, sugar and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in wok.
Cook peanuts until browned; set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil to wok and heat.
Cook chili peppers until charred on medium heat. Increase heat to high and cook chicken for 2 minutes.
Add onions, peanuts and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Can be frozen at this point.
Mix 1/2 stick oleo and corn flakes for top.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla and oatmeal. Drop on cookie sheet, 1/2 teaspoon of dough 2-inches apart.
They spread.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes at 375°.
Let sit a couple of minutes before removing.
Tastes good and looks pretty.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar.
Knead with fingers.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: southwestern success
directions: Prepare rice.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rice and cheese.
Remove from heat.
Add cooked rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients. Mix the cranberries and confectioner sugar and let stand 1/2 hour. Then fold into muffin batter. Fill 12 well greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: florida spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook pasta 7 minutes from boiling. Heat tomato sauce and garlic in saucepan.
Mix with drained pasta and place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Lay cheese on top and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add milk and vanilla.
Make dough soft but easy to handle. Chill.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut your favorite designs.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water 5 minutes. Save 5 tablespoons juice. Add soda when cool.
Beat oleo and sugar.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk 5 minutes.
Beat in the eggs; stir in the brown sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together and stir into mixture.
Stir in the oil.
Grease muffin cups and spoon in the muffin mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: jan's bean delight
directions: Throw it together and cook forever in crock-pot.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt together in pan.
Add egg yolk, 3/4 cup milk and chocolate.
When chocolate is melted use mixer on low speed to get smooth.
Let cool (not jelled).
Whip milk (cold) until peaks form.
Add chocolate mixture.
You may fold together with the mixer.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 more minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool, but do not let it jell.
When cool, add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour into a serving bowl.

title: hot baked fruit
directions: Place prunes, apricots and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine cherry pie filling, water and sherry or juice.
Pour over fruit.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Delicious with meats.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Freeze overnight.
Let set 30 to 40 minutes before serving.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Blend in lemon juice and milk. Add sugar, flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whites. Pour into ungreased 1 quart casserole dish.
Place dish in a pan of very hot water, one inch deep.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm or cool and add whipped cream or ice cream if desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from broth and let cool.
Boil rice, onion, carrots, celery, spices and butter in chicken broth (vegetables should be crisp).
Remove chicken from bones.
Add the chicken to the prepared rice.
Heat and serve.

title: fat free oven fried potatoes
directions: Spray the bottom of a baking dish with Pam cooking spray. Spread potatoes in dish; spray potatoes.
Spread onions on top of potatoes; spray with Pam.
Continue the same procedure with the green peppers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 375° until tender.

title: vegetable cream soup
directions: Peel and cut carrots, potatoes and onions to desired size. Cover with water and boil (steam) until soft.
Add milk to vegetables and bring to a boil.
Add a pinch of soda and can of diced tomatoes.
Add a light thickener made with cornstarch and milk.
Bring to a boil again.
(When milk is added, stir frequently or it will stick; also be sure to add baking soda before tomatoes.)

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring to boil, sugar and Karo syrup.
Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Mix with Rice Krispies.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Coat cutlets with nonstick cooking spray and place in heated skillet.
Saute on each side for 2 minutes.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add oil to skillet and saute garlic; return chicken to skillet and simmer for 5 minutes.
Ready in 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Also great over pasta.

title: stove top macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Leave in pot and mix in margarine, salt and pepper to taste, eggs and milk for consistency desired.
Add cheese.
Let simmer long enough for cheese to melt.

title: chicken 'n dumplings(for 4 people)
directions: Put water, chicken, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes in a large pot.
Boil until chicken falls off bone.
Remove all bones from chicken and pot.
If dry, add 1/2 cup hot water.
Take 1 cup of broth from chicken.
Add flour to medium bowl.
Push around edge of bowl.
Put 2 tablespoons of broth into center of bowl.
Add flour with teaspoon.
Stir together to make ball size dumplings. When through, put on medium flame.
Cook 1 hour.

title: almost sugarless pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with small amount of saved pineapple juice. Beat in pineapple. Add pudding. Stir in cherries, pecan pieces and Cool-Whip. Mix well. Pour into Pie shell and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook the rice and cool; then mix all ingredients together. Add salt to taste.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: beef hash and eggs
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil and butter over medium heat.
Add potatoes and cook without stirring for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender and lightly browned.
In small bowl, with fork, gradually stir beef broth into flour until smooth.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
With spatula, firmly flatten and cook without stirring for 5 minutes until sauce is thickened. Next, stir in roast beef.
Make shallow indents in hash and break an egg into each one.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes until eggs are cooked as desired.
Sprinkle with parsley or onion and serve.

title: shrimp perleau
directions: Cut up shrimp, if large.
Fry bacon in pan.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Cover and cook on low heat until tender.
Add shrimp, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Cook 6 minutes.
Add cooked rice.
Stir well to mix.
Will serve 6.

title: pepper cheese grits(even those who don't like grits, like this!)
directions: Stir grits into boiling salted water.
Cover and cook slowly 25 to 30 minutes.
Add all cheese except 3/4 cup and stir until melted.
Blend a small amount of grits into beaten eggs, then stir eggs into grits.
Add garlic powder if used.
Pour into a greased two-quart casserole; sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Cool and cover.
May be kept in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, basil and salt.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: honolulu heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate topping and 1/4 cup of the nuts.
Pour int 8 x 11-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with nuts saved and chocolate topping over the top.
Freeze until firm and slice.

title: black devil's food cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix cocoa in hot water; add margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Form into rolls to be sliced.
Chill again.
Slice and bake as desired, for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee can pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add all liquids and pumpkin.
Stir until smooth.
Grease and flour four 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill half full with batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mary wolf's nut roll
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until it looks like coarse meal.
Add yolks and sour cream.
Blend well, with hands. Cut dough into 6 sections, wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, pecans, raisins, cherries and pineapple.
In a pan, combine marshmallows, milk and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Pour over pecan mixture and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: russian fluff
directions: Fry hamburg and onion.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetarian tomato spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in cooking oil.
Add chopped tomatoes, water, paste, bouillon, spices and cooking wine.
Simmer.
Chop vegetables, using whichever vegetables you prefer.
Add generous amounts to sauce.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve hot over pasta.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve hot with Melba toast, crisp crackers, etc.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, tartar, water and oil in large pan.
Cook over low heat.
Use wooden spoon to stir until mixture is like dough.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
When cool, add flavoring and coloring.
Knead until smooth.

title: "braggin best" sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine, vegetable oil and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.

title: spiced apple muffins(15 large muffins)
directions: Combine dry ingredients; make a well in center of mixture. Combine milk, shortening and egg; add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in order given.
Serve with Doritos.

title: italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing overnight.
Roll chicken in crushed crackers and then in Parmesan cheese.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Place coated chicken in casserole dish.
Spread remaining crackers and cheese over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue cooking until brown.

title: no-cook noodles lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine browned ground beef, oregano and spaghetti sauce.
Layer sauce, noodles and a mixture of eggs, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese between layers.
Reserve 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole after baking.
Pour water evenly into 4 corners of dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: parmesan chicken picatta
directions: Rinse chicken pieces with water; do not dry.
Coat chicken with combined Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Brown chicken for 5 minutes on each side or until lightly browned and tender.
Remove chicken to platter.
Keep warm.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add wine to skillet; stir to loosen drippings.
Remove from heat and serve over chicken.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth at least 5 minutes.
(Can use frozen broccoli, also.)
Saute onion and carrots in margarine until clear.
Add flour to make a roux (thickening sauce).
Add pepper to taste.
Add half and half.
Cook until thickened.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice. Stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold flour mixture into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a towel sprinkled with 10x sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool and unroll.

title: cherry cheese cake ice cream
directions: Prepare no bake cheese cake crumbs according to package directions, using margarine and sugar; set aside.

Prepare cheese cake filling according to package directions, using milk; fold in whipped topping. Spoon half of the filling mixture into a large bowl. Cover with prepared crumbs and cherry pie filling.
Top with remaining filling mixture.
Pull metal spatula through mixture several times to marble.
Do not overmix.
Cover and freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving. Scoop into individual dishes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients with fruit cocktail; mix well.
Place coconut in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and pour cake batter on top.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, onion and pepper.
Brush on both sides of eggplant; dip in cracker crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven, turning once until browned, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Always soak sliced eggplant in salted water about 30 minutes before cooking.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast with water.
Mix rest of ingredients; mix well. Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll out on greased sheet tray.
Makes one normal size pizza crust.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine the egg and milk; mix well.
Stir together the flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices in egg mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Fry tomato slices in hot oil until browned, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: jewish noodles
directions: Boil noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain, then add butter, sour cream, cottage cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple (do not drain).
Mix together and put in greased pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar before baking.

title: new england squash pie
directions: Combine squash, sugar, eggs, milk and spices.
Pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° until of a custard consistency, about 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until browned.
Reduce heat to 300°
and bake until done 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool before serving.
Yields 2 pies.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together pudding mix and milk. Fold in cool whip.
Put in a single layer of crackers of bottom of a 9x13 dish.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Place another layer of crackers on top of pudding mix.
Add remaining pudding mixture.
Place another layer of crackers.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl; mix well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead dough 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Bake pie crust at preheated 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Distribute tuna over the bottom of pastry shell. Sprinkle cheese and onion over tuna.
Beat eggs; add milk, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour over tuna mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until top is golden.
Remove from oven and let set a few minutes before cutting.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray shallow baking dish with cooking spray.

title: stack up ole
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add green pepper. Cook until tender. Combine process cheese, picante sauce and milk in saucepan. Stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted. Add meat mixture and olives. Mix well. Place one tortilla in baking dish. Top with 1/4 of meat mixture. Repeat layers, ending with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Serve garnished with sour cream and tomato wedges.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw and drain broccoli.
In a large bowl, mix broccoli, mushroom soup, mayo, egg and Velveeta cheese. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: everybody's favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: aunt karilene's mock apple pie
directions: Roll out bottom crust of pastry and fit into 9-inch pie plate. Break Ritzs coarsely into pastry-lined plate.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan; boil gently for 15 minutes. Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.

title: christmas divinity
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, melt shortening; add cocoa and stir until smooth.
Set aside over warm water.
In large saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water; cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Lower heat slightly and cook uncovered, without stirring, to 260° (hard-ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Immediately, pour syrup in a thin stream into egg whites, beating on high speed of electric mixer.
Add vanilla; beat until candy begins to hold its shape.
Quickly blend in cocoa mixture, nuts and cherries.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: date nut bread
directions: Boil the dates in the water.
Let cool 1/2 hour.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add the remaining ingredients. Add date liquid alternately with flour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Crumble cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Make pudding as directed on package. Add 3 tablespoons Cool Whip.
Pour over cake crumbs and add strawberries. Add the remaining Cool Whip and top with coconut and nuts.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add all ingredients together in large boiler.
Can double recipe.
Cook on low heat 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Continually Stir.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Combine ground beef and onion; cook until meat is browned and crumbles.
Drain, stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini and peppers
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook onion in hot oil for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender. Stir in zucchini, roasted pepper, water, and cumin. Reduce heat; simmer covered, for 3 to 5 minutes or until zucchini is crisp-tender. Add salt and pepper to taste. Transfer mixture to a serving bowl; top with cheese. Yield: 6 side-dish servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Line the bottom of the pan with waxed paper and grease it, too.
Drain salmon and remove skin and bones.
In a small skillet; cook celery and onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Remove from heat.
In a medium size bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in bread crumb mixture, milk, parsley, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Fold in salmon and lemon juice until well blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let loaf stand for about 3 minutes.
Loosen around the sides with a spatula and turn out onto a heated serving platter. Carefully remove waxed paper.
Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from beans; mix ingredients all together.
Chill if desired and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese
and
taco
seasoning.
Refrigerate
8 hours. Spread in bottom
of
bowl.
Sprinkle shredded lettuce over cream cheese mixture.
Put diced tomatoes on top of that. Sprinkle shredded cheese over
all.
To serve, put nacho chips around sides of bowl.

title: broccoli-onion casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well; set aside.
Cook frozen or fresh onions in boiling, salted water, about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain; set aside.

title: easy dill onion bread
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour with the yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, butter, salt, dill seed and onion until warm, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool if above 115°.
Add to dry mixture.
Add egg.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes.
(An easy way to do this is to put bowl in your oven and add a pan of hot water on lower shelf and close the door).
Stir down.
Spread evenly in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or a large round casserole.
Let rise until nearly doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil if bread browns too quickly.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter.
Add rice.
Heat on low for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, spinach and cheese. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Top with extra cheese.
Makes 5 cups.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: In skillet, combine sugar, candies and water.
Stir over medium heat until sugar and candies dissolve.
Core the apples; cut crosswise in 1/2-inch rings.
Add to syrup.
Simmer gently until transparent, but not soft.
Cool in syrup.

title: fermented fruit cake or friendship cake
directions: Day One:
Pour starter into glass gallon jar.
Add can of sliced peaches and juice (cut each slice into four pieces).
Add 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir.
Cover jar loosely and keep at room temperature.
Stir every day for ten days.
All the sugar may not dissolve for several days.
Don't cover airtight.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, partially drain.
Fry hamburger and onions in bacon fat.
Combine all ingredients and put in baking casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamed leek soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan cook the leeks or onions in a small amount of boiling water, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain and save water to use later.
In same pan melt margarine and stir in flour, bouillon granules and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add milk and the saved 1 cup water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add shredded cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Add cooked onions; heat through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Chop bacon in 1 inch pieces and cook until browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Chop onion and add to ground beef and brown.
Drain and rinse all beans except the pork and beans.
Drain beef, add reserve beans, pork and beans (undrained), barbecue sauce, and all except 1/4 of bacon and mix well.
Spoon mixture into baking pan and top with remaining bacon. Bake 45 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar while continuing to
beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oil and vanilla. Fold in apples.
Pour into a greased 9 x 15-inch pan. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beans until soft, not mushy. Put all, including juice, in roaster and mix (if too much juice, add gradually).
Bake at 425° for 2 hours, covered.
Stir and check every 1/2 hour.
To brown, bake, uncovered, last 1/2 hour.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Simmer ingredients in a large, nonstick skillet for 1 hour. You can cook this in a crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours while you are away from the house.
Calories per serving: 121.
Fat per serving: 1 gram.
Protein per serving: 16 grams.

title: baked bean quintet
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat and onion.
Add bacon and rest of ingredients.
Stir gently with a spoon to mix.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine cornstarch, garlic, onions and salt.
Add chicken and toss to coat the chicken.
Prepare broccoli (steam) and drain in a large skillet.
Add 1/2 the oil to chicken mixture.
Stir-fry until chicken loses its color, about 2 minutes on high heat.
Add oil and pepper.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add broccoli.
Stir-fry.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer 1 minute.
Serve over rice (hot).
I add cut onions, sliced potatoes, cabbage, snow peas and yellow squash.

title: bob evans breakfast
directions: Brown sausage; drain on paper towel.
Take 6 slices of bread and break up on bottom of pan.
Put sausage on top of bread.
Put cubed cheese on top of sausage, next sprinkle onion, green pepper and ham on top of cheese (optional).
Take milk and eggs and beat. Pour over everything in pan.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let cool for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix oil, sugar and eggs for 2 minutes. Add flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla and coloring. Pour into greased and floured pans. Makes 3 layers. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool completely before icing.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Rub ribs with crushed garlic; cut into serving size pieces. Place the ribs in a large, shallow pan; set aside.
Heat oil in a skillet; add onion and cook until tender, stirring occasionally. Blend in tomato sauce, water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt and pepper; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs and marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Remove ribs from marinade (reserve for brushing) and put on grill or in a basket broiler 5-inches from coals.
Grill 1 hour or until done, turning and brushing frequently with marinade.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease one bread loaf pan. Combine all ingredients. Stir with a spoon about 60 strokes. Stir in nuts. Pour into pan. Bake for 45-55 minutes. Use a toothpick to check for doneness. Cool for 15 minutes. Top with powdered sugar frosting thinned to a drizzle topping consistency. Let cool completely before slicing.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Cut up broccoli; peel and chop stems.
Simmer in 1/2 cup of the water until just tender.
Add soup, seasonings and water.
Cook until well blended and hot, but not boiling; stir occasionally. Stir in grated cheese until melted.
Serve hot.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Cover fish with batter; fry until golden brown.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut onions in rings.
Mix all ingredients except onions together.
Dip onions in mixture.
Deep fry until brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in berries.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix sugar, pretzels and melted margarine; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
This will be bubbly when taken from oven.
Set aside to cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar; beat together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread mixture over cooled crust in pan.
Spread slightly thickened jello mixture on top.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: fredie's apple cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Stir into the next 6 combined ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle on top.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked apples
directions: Place apples close together in an 8-inch square pan and pour soda over them.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over them and bake until soft.
Try strawberry or raspberry cream soda.
Serve with a peak of whipped topping.
Apples are good hot or cold.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chiles in a layer over bottom of dish.
Cover with cheese.
Blend eggs, salt, milk and Bisquick mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make dressing. Marinate broccoli in dressing.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. (Keeps well overnight or several nights!)
Before serving, add bacon and raisins.

title: progressive farmer fruit cake
directions: Empty cake mix into bowl and add applesauce, eggs, salt and juice.
Beat 3 minutes or until creamy and smooth.
Combine fruits and nuts and dredge them in the flour.
Stir into the batter.
Line 2 (8 x 4 x 3-inch) loaf pans with a triple thickness of waxed paper and grease well.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 275° for 2 hours and 45 minutes.
Cool cakes on a rack until thoroughly cool. Remove from pans leaving paper attached to cakes.
Wrap cakes in aluminum foil and refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.
Yields 2 large or 4 small loaves.

title: grape syrup
directions: In small bowl, stir
jam
until
smooth.
Stir in syrup until well blended.
Delicious over pancakes, waffles or pound cake. Will keep in refrigerator.	Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: ziti
directions: Boil shell macaroni until done.
Drain.
Mix the cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, basil and shells. Top with Prego sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: brussel sprout and tomato salad
directions: Cook brussel sprouts according to directions on pkg.
Mix vinegar, oil, chervil, salt,
and pepper in tightly covered jar. Pour over hot brussel sprouts.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours. Before serving, add sliced tomato or cherry tomatoes or grape tomatoes.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley.

title: the fitt ball
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, Accent, onions, Worcestershire sauce and 1 bag of dried beef; mix well with those little hands until well blended.
(It will be firm.)
Roll into a ball and roll in the remaining dried beef.
Can be made 5 days ahead.
I keep remaining dried beef and roll it a second time before serving.

title: potato and carrot packets on grill
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and carrots about 1/4 inch.
Peel onion; slice thin.
Tear off 4 pieces of heavy-duty foil about 18 x 12-inches.
Rub some butter into the center of each piece. Distribute evenly the potatoes, carrots and onion onto the foil. Add salt, pepper and pats of butter.
Fold up packets, closing off the ends.
Place on a hot grill and cook for about 45 minutes, turning once during cooking.

title: schaum torte
directions: Sprinkle salt over egg whites and beat until frothy. Add cream of tartar and beat until the bowl can be turned upside down and hold the whites. Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time and beat until dissolved. Just before the last tablespoon of sugar, add vanilla, vinegar and almond extract. Then beat in final tablespoon of sugar. Scoop with large kitchen spoon a full helping of meringue. Dent and swirl. Put on brown paper (grocery sacks or parcel post) that has been greased with cooking oil. Put brown paper on cookie sheets and bake at 225° for about 1 1/2 hours. Turn off and cool in the oven. Be careful not to burn. This can only be done on a dry, sunny day!

title: nana's baked spaghetti(great for picnics and buffets)
directions: Cook beef and drain well.
Cook onion and green pepper until soft in lightly coated fry pan; use olive oil.
Season with garlic powder if desired.
Cover bottom of pan with a layer of sauce. Layer with cooked spaghetti.
Next a layer of ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Top with sauce.
Continue layers until pan is full, ending with a layer of spaghetti.
Cover with sauce.
Top with large amount of Cheddar cheese to make a thick layer.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes until hot through and cheese is melted. Cover with foil if cheese gets too brown.
Serve with extra sauce if desired.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar mixed with cornstarch or flour. Mix
and
add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell
and sprinkle
with
nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set and slightly brown.

title: garbage cake
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple and nuts together. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pie filling mixture. Cut butter into approximately 10 to 12 pats and place on top of cake mix. Do not stir. Cover with coconut. Bake at 350° until coconut is golden brown.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk and beat well.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Cream cheese should be softened.
Grate cucumber. Drain well. Add cream cheese and mix well.
Add nuts and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Mix until combined.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Knead real well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix with sweet milk or buttermilk; fry in hot oil.
Makes large serving.

title: parmesan biscuits
directions: Dip each biscuit into butter; roll in Parmesan cheese to coat. Arrange biscuits in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Bake at 450° until golden brown and crusty.
Makes 20 servings.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling. Cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, onions, green peppers and cheese in pie plate.

title: mock pate
directions: Mix liverwurst, chopped onions and mayonnaise into a ball, using milk and Tabasco sauce to soften cream cheese.
Cover ball with the cheese mixture and roll it in the minced parsley.
Cool to firm it and serve with crackers.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Cook bacon in skillet; remove bacon.
Mix together potatoes, cabbage and seasoning.
Flatten mixture in skillet.
When browned on one side, turn and brown on the other.
May add crumbled bacon to mixture.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and fill graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: peppered pan potatoes
directions: In small bowl, combine salt, pepper, basil and thyme.
Place 2 tablespoons of butter in 10-inch nonstick skillet.
Line the bottom of skillet with overlapping slices of potatoes in circular pattern; sprinkle with part of salt mixture, 2 tablespoons of onion and 4 tablespoons of butter.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 11x7 inch baking dish.
Cook beef and onion in large skillet until beef is browned, drain.
Stir in taco sauce, water, chilies and seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cook, stirring occasionally for 3 to 4 minutes.
Layer half of broken shells on bottom of prepared baking dish.
Cover with half of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, sliced green onions and sour cream.
Yield 8 servings.

title: nonfat eggnog
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, heat 5 cups milk, Egg Beaters and sugar until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and rum extract.
Cover and chill. Just before serving, thin with one cup skim milk and garnish with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serves 8.

title: batter fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, milk, egg, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Cut boneless chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Sprinkle with salt and dip into batter.
Fry in deep, hot fat until done and golden brown.

title: doubly good yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix 2 minutes on low speed of electric mixer and set aside.
Combine flour with remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix 3 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add yeast mixture and mix well at medium speed.
Cover and let rise in warm place until dough has doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shape in desired rolls and brush with melted butter. Let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, about 2 hours, or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown on top.
Top with slivered almonds.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin gingerbread
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, granulated sugar and orange juice in a bowl until smooth.
Add egg whites, one at a time until blended.
Stir in pumpkin, corn syrup and molasses.

title: parmesan cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine the flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Place 6 to 8 pieces of potato in bag at a time.
Shake to coat.
Place coated pieces of potato in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in which you have melted the butter.
Put potatoes in a single layer.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
After 1/2 hour, turn potatoes and sprinkle with remaining flour and cheese mixture.
When done, they will be golden brown, crunchy on the outside and soft on the inside.
Preparation time: 15 minutes; cooking time: 1 hour.
Quick and easy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick and easy deep fry batter
directions: Add water to make a thin batter.
If cooking fish, cut and salt.
Dip in batter and deep fry until done.

title: chewy tan bars
directions: Melt margarine; add sugars, egg and vanilla and beat well. Add nuts; stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Spread in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bessie's squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash 7 - 10 minutes or until fork tender; drain and mash slightly.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour into casserole dish and top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: deviled ham puffs
directions: Blend cream cheese, baking powder, milk and egg yolk together. Toast bread on one side.
Spread untoasted side with deviled ham. Cover with a mound of cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until puffed and slightly browned.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Whisk in milk until smooth, then yolks until blended.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Add butter and whisk constantly over medium heat 5 to 7 minutes just until boiling.
Remove from heat and stir 1 minute longer.
Cover with plastic and cool.
Stir in sour cream until blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover loosely and refrigerate at least 6 hours or up to 2 days.
Before serving, add garnishes. Serves 8.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook meat, onions and pepper until pink is gone.
Add taco seasoning and Ranch dip, then the rest of ingredients.
Use as much water that you need to make the consistency you want.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Top with grated cheese of choice.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in pan and blend in flour.
Add milk and other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until smooth and thick (approximately 7 minutes). Serve over broccoli or cauliflower.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together tomato paste, tomato sauce, Ragu, package of spaghetti sauce mix and cooked ground chuck. Cook noodles in large amount of water until tender; drain and rinse. Mix eggs, cottage cheese, parmesan cheese, salt, parsley flakes and pepper. Layer noodles. Spread cottage cheese filling, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce. Repeat steps until done. Top with cheese. Bake at 375 degrees about 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Use for barbecued chicken or beef.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sausage treats
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into approximately 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
After thoroughly mixing, remove half of the ingredients to another container.
Add ice to the top of the blender and mix with the remaining half of the ingredients.
Repeat with other half and serve.

title: baked brie in bread
directions: Slice top of the bread off.
Scoop out bread from crust.
Cut or tear bread into pieces and toast to serve with Brie.
Butter inside of crust.
Layer the Brie, mushrooms, garlic and toasted almonds on the inside of crust.
Place the top back onto the round.
Loosely cover with aluminum foil.
Place the round on a cookie sheet.
Heat in a 300° oven for about 20 minutes or until cheese has melted and ingredients are easily mixed.
Keep aluminum foil on top and return to oven.
Heat thoroughly (about 10 to 15 minutes or more).
Serve with toasted pieces of bread.

title: stuffed veal cutlets(vitello cotoletta ripieni)
directions: From my husband's Aunt Dora.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake until brown on top at 375°.

title: luscious carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Make cheese sauce in normal manner.
In buttered baking dish, put alternating layers of carrots, sauce and onion rings.
Reserve some onion rings for topping.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Put remainder of onion rings on last 5 minutes.

title: sweet and sour glazed ham
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Slice away skin from ham.
Score fat on ham in diamond design and stud with whole cloves.
Place ham, fat side up, on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat or bone.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Baste every 15 to 20 minutes with sauce.
Yields 10 to 14 servings.

title: english connection scones
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Cut butter into pats and combine with flour until it resembles fine bread crumbs.
Add whipping cream.
Turn on floured bread board.
Knead lightly, 3 or 4 times.
Pat out to 1-inch thick. Cut out round with glass or cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 12 scones.

title: green beans and carrots almondine(microwave)
directions: Combine carrots, green beans, bouillon cube and water in 2-quart casserole, cover and cook on High in microwave for 12 to 14 minutes until tender-crisp, stirring twice while cooking.
In a 1 cup measuring cup, cook butter and slivered almonds until lightly browned.
Add lemon juice and toss with cooked vegetables.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescents and press firmly in a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and dressing until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, boiled eggs or your favorite salad toppings.

title: frozen grapes with frangelico
directions: Remove stems from grapes and wash thoroughly.
Place grapes on a tray lined with paper towels and freeze until hard.
Serve in dessert dishes with a glass of Frangelico or with a little Frangelico sprinkled on the grapes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until sugar is melted; do not boil! Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and beat in milk, butter, bananas and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Bake each pancake on a hot, lightly oiled griddle, pouring out 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake.
Flip once when brown.

title: sweet pickles(8-day)
directions: Wash cucumbers and put into crock whole; cover with boiling water.
Repeat with boiling water 3 mornings.
The fifth morning, drain, then slice or cut in chunks or slice longways.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Cook in double boiler until fairly thick.
Remove from heat; add beaten egg yolks and butter.
Cool somewhat.
Add the stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into a baking dish or casserole; bake in a slow oven (325°) for about 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Add plenty of butter at the table, as for any hot bread.
Especially good with baked or fried ham.

title: trail bars
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with no-stick spray.
Measure out cereal.
Cut up fruits and nuts and have all measured and ready to add before melting marshmallows.
Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir almost continuously until melted and well blended.
Remove pot from heat and quickly stir in remaining ingredients, stirring until well coated.
Pour into sprayed pan and allow to cool.
Cut into bars and wrap each bar in foil, for hiking.
These travel and keep well.

title: pasta bruccoleri(on a healthy note)
directions: Steam vegetables.
Cook pasta.
Saute garlic in 1/4 cup of chicken broth.
Add steamed vegetables, pasta and remainder of chicken broth to garlic.
Add margarine (optional).
Sprinkle grated Parmesan over pasta to serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into 9-inch uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green party salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in top of a double boiler.
Pour hot mixture over lime gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese.
When cheese is dissolved, add pineapple.
Cool. Blend in mayonnaise, whipped cream and nuts (if desired).
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until fluffy.
Serve with any kind of fruit.

title: 4 layer pudding
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts until crumbly. Press in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° on top rack for 20 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: cherry crunch cake bars
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts and put in long pan.
Press it out to make
a
crust.
Bake
at
350° until brown.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar and pour over crust after
crust cools.
Pour
cherry
filling
over
filling and refrigerate.

title: parmesan potato casserole
directions: Lightly grease shallow baking dish.
Cook potatoes and drain. Return to pot, add butter and mash.
Add milk, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper and mash until smooth.
Spoon into prepared dish.
Bake uncovered 35-45 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine flour, sugar, egg, reserved pineapple juice and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix with remaining ingredients and 1/2 of the nuts. Sprinkle with remaining nuts on top.
Refrigerate until served.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cream cheese, 1 tablespoon sugar and lemon juice.
Place in refrigerator to set slightly.
Crush crackers to make crumbs; add 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Place graham cracker crumb mixture in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save about 1 cup of crumbs for topping.
Whip chilled milk; add 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add cream cheese mixture and mix well.
Pour over crumbs and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini until al dente or firm.
Drain and rinse with cold water, then drain thoroughly.
Empty pasta into large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of prepared dressing.
Mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: cake with chocolate sauce
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Bring the following items to a boil: butter, water, salad oil and cocoa.
Pour over sugar and flour. Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stir-fried steak
directions: Cut steak with the grain into 2-inch wide strips.
Then cut each strip across the grain into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In a medium bowl, combine the steak and soy sauce, 1 tablespoon oil and 2 teaspoons cornstarch.
Stir to coat steak and set aside.

title: supreme hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Set out 8-inch square pan.
Blend flour into soup in saucepan. Add 3/4 cup milk and heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in chicken, pimiento and onion.
Cool slightly.
Spread mixture in pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 4 squares.
Place one square on each of 4 bread slices.
Cover with remaining bread slices.
Smooth edges with metal spatula.
Cut each sandwich in half to form rectangles.
Beat eggs with 1/4 cup milk. Dip sandwiches on all sides in egg mixture, then in potato chips. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: all-bran rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, All-Bran and salt in bowl, add boiling water.
Let stand until lukewarm, add well beaten eggs; mix with first mixture.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in the lukewarm water, then flour.
Roll out on well floured board, about 1/2-inch thick, cut with biscuit cutter.
Fold over halfway for pocketbook rolls, brush with melted butter before folding.
Let rise and bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be refrigerated up to 2 weeks.
Keep a damp cloth over top.
Can be made in any shape.
These are good light rolls that I use often.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Beat yolks till thick and lemon color.
Add water and beat. Add sugar gradually and beat thoroughly.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix until smooth; add vanilla.
Beat egg whites till foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Fold into cake batter.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan at 325°for 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert pan to cool.
Remove cake and frost.

title: easy low-fat vegetarian chili
directions: Cook carrots and celery with salt and pepper until tender in separate pot.
Combine all other ingredients and cook on medium heat 15 minutes.
Add drained carrots and celery; cook on low 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix ingredients together and spread evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cut up vegetables in a large bowl.
Add the jar of pimentos; cut if big pieces.
Add the bottle of dressing.
Add as many Bac*Os as you want.
Season with the seasoning to your taste.

title: three bean chili
directions: In 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, brown ground beef with onions and green pepper; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato soup and taco seasoning mix; blend well.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans; simmer an additional 15 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Makes 7 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: char's barbecued ribs
directions: Bake ribs in a 350° oven until done.
Top with sauce and brown 1/2 hour.

title: ranch vegetable dip
directions: Mix sour cream and dressing mix. Serve with your favorite fresh vegetables.

title: lemon bisque(yields 10 servings)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar, salt, juice and grated rind.
Refrigerate.
Whip the milk until stiff.
When the Jell-O is slightly congealed, add it to the whipped milk.
In a casserole pan, put a layer of crumbs; pour the Jell-O mixture over crumbs and cover the top with more crumbs.
Refrigerate until firm; cut into 3-inch squares.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into pie shells; bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then turn temperature down to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Work together flour, margarine (oleo) and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown lightly at 400° and let cool.

title: opryland bread pudding
directions: Break bread in small pieces in baking dish (about 1 1/2-quart).
Sprinkle cinnamon over bread and add raisins and melted butter.
Toast bread mixture lightly in 350° oven.
Mix eggs, sugar, milk and extract; add to bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until solid.

title: raisin pie
directions: Steam raisins in boiling water 25 minutes.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add flour; mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Use another pie shell to make strips for top of pie; dab dots of butter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: oven stew
directions: Cut up carrots, potatoes and green pepper.
Put in heavy roaster.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add seasonings and tapioca. Cover tightly and bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in milk, vanilla and dry ingredients (well sifted).
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: For German Chocolate Cake Mix Base:
Mix cake mix with 2 of the 4 eggs.
Mixture will be thick.
Put stick of butter in 9 x 12-inch cake pan and melt in oven.
Make sure all of pan gets greased by butter, then pour the excess into cake mixture.
Mix well.

title: snowflakes
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar well.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and orange rind.
Gradually blend in flour, salt and cinnamon which have been sifted together.
Fill press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake.
Remove at once.

title: "cheezed" potatoes
directions: Place top chafing pan in water jacket.
Melt butter.
Add onion and saute.
Place layer of potatoes in pan.
Add salt and cover potatoes with layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until all are used.
Pour the bouillon over this.
Cover pan and cook slowly, 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and piping hot.
Serve with salad or cold cuts.
Serves 4.

title: civitan fruit cake cookies(tv recipe)
directions: Mix cake mix,
oil,
flavoring and eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Add
fruit cake bits.
Roll in soft balls about the size of	walnuts.
Place
on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.

title: pineapple layer cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and egg.
One at a time, beating well after each.

title: chuck's crisp chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 16 minutes.

title: canuck pie
directions: Line a 10-inch pie pan with pastry.
Combine meats and cook, stirring, until meat particles separate, about 10 minutes.
Boil potatoes and onions together until tender.
Drain and mash, adding some of the potato liquid.
Add the spices, meat and some of the pan drippings.
Combine well.
Turn into the pastry-lined pan. Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in top crust; bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
When reheating use 350° oven for a few minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: wally's chili
directions: Brown meat in bacon drippings.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Add enough water to make correct consistency.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Never use a lid when making chili.
Simmer longer for a more spicy chili.
Do not put beans or anything else in this chili.
It will only take away from the flavor.

title: italian vegetarian stew
directions: In large skillet use part of the oil and brown zucchini, onions and mushrooms.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside in a dish.
In the same skillet, add remaining oil, if needed, and fry green and red peppers.
While peppers are frying, pour crushed tomatoes in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Put in green beans and cook until tender (do not overcook beans).
Add salt, pepper and red crushed pepper to taste.
(Should have a bit of a bite to it.)
When beans are al dente, combine all veggies to sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Take off heat and let set for 5 minutes.
Serve over pasta or eat plain with bread.

title: confetti punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and mint leaves.
Chill.
Strain.
Pour mixture over ice in a bowl.
Pour ginger ale and soda water in on sides of bowl to create foam.
Add fruit sherbet scoops to float on top.

title: scotch pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs until frothy.
Add salt, sugar, vanilla and almond.
Alternate flour, milk and yogurt.
Add any optional ingredients.
Just before cooking, add baking powder.
Stir briefly until the lumps are out.
Cook on a very hot griddle without oil.
These pancakes are magic; they don't stick because of the baking powder.
Serve hot and add fresh fruit, maple syrup or yogurt.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all ingredients to large loaf pan; shake ketchup over top and pieces of block cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
(It will thicken when done.)

title: real rice
directions: Heat oil and garlic on high.
Stir in rice to coat with oil. Add water (it will sizzle).
Cook on high to boil off water (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Uncover and stir the liquid.
It should be almost gone.
Turn off heat and let stand.
Serve with Spanish or Chinese recipes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add can of pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients, add to mixture and then add water.
Mix well.
Raisins and nuts may be added if desired.
Makes 2 loaves, 3 medium loaves or 4 small loaves.
Grease pans and bake in a 350° oven; large loaves for 1 hour, medium loaves for 40 minutes and small loaves for 30 minutes.
Toothpick comes out clean when done.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees until done and brown on top.
Let loaves cool slightly in pans.
Pour glaze over loaves and cook completely in pan before removing.
Makes 3 small or 2 large loaves.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare noodles as directed.
Drain and mix ingredients together.
Put mixture into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion; add paste and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Spoon onto buns.
Top with cheese. These open-faced sandwiches can be placed in a 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: cherry cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package except bake 20 minutes.
Beat vanilla, egg, milk and cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth.
Pour over baked brownie layer. Bake until topping is set, approximately 25 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.
Top with pie filling.
