Store in refrigerator.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: frank alper's man's barbecue chicken
directions: Day before or early in the day, in saucepan, make sauce. Combine salt, pepper, tomato juice, cayenne, mustard, sugar, bay leaf, vinegar, Worcestershire, garlic and oleo.
Simmer 10 minutes, then refrigerate.

title: toscas
directions: Cream 6 tablespoons butter and add gradually 1/4 cup sugar. Blend in 1 cup sifted flour.
Divide into 12 small ungreased muffin tins.
Press into bottoms and halfway up sides of cups. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: festive carrot apple salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Can be made several hours before mealtime.

title: banana pudding 1(noncooked kind)
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream. Crumble vanilla wafers in pan or dish.
Layer wafers, bananas and mixture.

title: breakfast in the car
directions: Stuff pita pocket with cream cheese, fruit and nuts.
Place on a paper towel and microwave on High 20 seconds.
Pack up and eat on the go.
Yields 1 serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Arrange broccoli and chicken in casserole dish.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, mushrooms and rice.
Pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over soups. Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly and the cheese is melted.

title: garden salad
directions: Bring sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, water to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Drain canned vegetables.
Mix all vegetables. Pour cooled liquid over vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.
Will keep a week.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, basil, parsley flakes, oregano and garlic salt to hamburger.
In separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, salami and eggs.

title: camp potatoes
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Place potatoes, onion and green pepper on heavy-duty foil; dot with butter.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over top.
Fold foil up around potatoes.
Be sure to seal edges of foil well.
Grill, covered, over medium coals for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onions.
In a six quart kettle, mix all ingredients together. Simmer for forty-five (45) minutes.

title: nacona's cookies
directions: Soak raisins in beaten egg and vanilla mixture until soft. Cream butter and white and brown sugars.
Add raisin and egg mixture.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add oats and nuts.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Put away in a covered container while still a little warm.

title: stickies
directions: Thaw frozen bread but do not let raise.
Pick thawed pieces off one loaf of bread and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sue's cream biscuits
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Cut in butter or margarine. Beat eggs (save a little of the white to spread on top of dough) and add to mixture.
Toss on a lightly floured board and roll to about 3/4-inch thickness.
Use a floured biscuit cutter to cut biscuits.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet and brush tops with egg white and sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and butter like pie crust and pat in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Mix apples, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spread over crust.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar in blender.
Pour into pot with sugar and cook until it becomes thick.
Pour into 2 uncooked pie crusts and bake for 30 to 45 minutes on 400°.

title: mississippi mud cake i(24 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).
Lightly grease one 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cream together 1/3 cup of the cocoa, white sugar and 1 cup of the butter or margarine until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs and 1 teaspoon of the vanilla and beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder, coconut and chopped pecans together.
Stir flour mixture into the egg mixture and stir until just combined. Pour batter into the prepared 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350°F (175°C) for 40 to 50 minutes.
Smooth Marshmallow Creme over top of cake while still hot.
Let cake cool completely then ice with Chocolate Icing.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on a greased baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven (300° to 350°) about 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: mom's munchers
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar, eggs and remaining ingredients. Butter a cookie pan and drop by small spoonfuls 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: ragtime rocky road
directions: Melt
chocolate
bars in top of double boiler over warm water; stir
in
marshmallows
and
nuts.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan. Chill. Cut when firm. Yields 16 squares.

title: margaritas
directions: Put all in blender, add ice, blend and serve.

title: beef dip
directions: Soak dried beef in hot water for 1 to 2 hours (to get out salt).
Ring out water.
Rinse.
Mix cream cheese and shredded cheese.
Mince beef.
Chop pepper.
Mix all ingredients together. Heat in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits and enjoy!!

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours or overnight.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, alternately with milk; begin and end with flour. Add flavorings.

title: baked ham steak
directions: Put ham steak in a microwave baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on Medium for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Drain and reserve juices.
Mix juices with brown sugar and mustard. Spread over top of steak.
Cook, uncovered, on Medium for 2 minutes.
Cover loosely and let stand for 2 or 3 minutes before serving.

title: country style cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, stir together the first six ingredients.
Add the next four ingredients and toss to coat well.
Cover and chill for several hours.
If desired, serve in a bowl lined with lettuce leaves.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: cajun rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown sausage in skillet with onion. Add Cajun spice and drain kidney beans.
Add to rice mixture and serve.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Place roast in a pan which has a cover.
Season both sides with salt and pepper.
Cover the pan with foil, crimping edges around pan.
Place the lid on the pan.
Do not add water and do not peek!
Bake 30 to 45 minutes per pound at 275° if roast is thawed and at 300° if roast is frozen.
The secret to the success of this roast is not looking.

title: chicken and biscuits with gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove skin from chicken and place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread undiluted soup over chicken. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and arrange biscuits on top of chicken.
Continue baking at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Mix and pour over the apples.
Mix reserved cake mix with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries up and soak in sugar for 2 hours.
Then mix the marshmallows, pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip with the berries.

title: orange bread
directions: Combine sugar, pecan and orange rind in a small bowl. Separate each biscuit; place a cream cheese square in center of one half and top with remaining half.
Pinch sides togehter.
Dip in butter and dredge in sugar mixture.
Stand each biscuit on edge in a lightly greased 12 cup bundt pan.
Spacing evenly, drizzle with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately invert onto a wire rack.
Combine powdered sugar and orange juice, spoon over warm bread.
Serve immediately.
Yield 1-10 inch coffee cake.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soups and sour cream together.
Divide in half.
Add chilies, onion, 1/2 the cheese, all the chicken to 1/2 the mixture. Roll mixture in tortillas and place in baking pan.
Cover with remainder of sauce and grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for several hours to blend flavors.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups sauce.
Use on spareribs or chicken.

title: saltless seasoning salt
directions: Mix together.
Cover.
Store in a dry place.
Use as you would regular seasoned salt.

title: flake cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Separately, cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mix and cereal last.
Don't over-blend the cereal.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet; bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add 2 Tbsp. of granulated sugar at a time, then same with powdered sugar, beating at high speed after each addition.
Butter and flour 9-inch pie pan and spread meringue evenly in pan.
Bake 300 for 45 - 50 minutes until lightly browned. Meringue will rise above pan but center will fall as it cools. Cool and fill.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in reserved juice. Add cheese and pineapple.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry ground meat with celery and broccoli
directions: In heavy large skillet or wok at high heat stir-fry meat until done, then add vegetables and stir-fry until broccoli turns color, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add spices and remaining ingredients, except cornstarch and water.
Stir to blend.
Add the cornstarch mixture and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until sauce thickens. Remove from heat and serve over rice or noodles.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Hollow 1 loaf of pumpernickel bread to make a bowl.
Fill with dip.
Cut another loaf of bread into 1-inch cubes to use for dipping. This also makes a great dip for veggies.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Mix sifted flour, baking powder and salt. Add alternately with milk. Beat until smooth. Pour in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch (or 1 1/2-quart) baking pan. Spoon fruit over. Sprinkle with sugar. Pour juice over all. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake.

title: fabulous make-ahead party potatoes(make these once, and you'll be famous for them!)
directions: Peel, cube and cook potatoes until tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain well; mash until smooth, adding a little milk if necessary (a KitchenAid-type mixer works well).
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings (except paprika) together.
Beat into potatoes with
whisk or blender until fluffy.
Taste for seasoning, adding what you think is necessary.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; sprinkle top with grated cheese, dots of butter and paprika. Cool, cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
(Flavor is best if casserole is refrigerated a day or two before serving.)

title: seafood okra gumbo
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, saving shells.
Set shrimp aside in refrigerator.
Boil shrimp shells in 2 quarts of water for several hours to make a stock.
Set aside.
In a heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of oil and saute the okra until all ropiness is gone, about 1/2 hour.
Set aside.

title: hot spiced grape punch
directions: Combine grape juice with water, sugar, cinnamon and ginger. Heat slowly, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Blend in lemon juice.
Serve with lemon slices pierced with cloves.

title: donna's frito pie
directions: Put layer of chili on bottom in dish (4 cans).
Cover with layer of Fritos, chopped onion and bits of cheese.
Repeat process of layering chili, Fritos, onion and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves several.
(Serve with salad and hot bread.)

title: harvest zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water.
Drain well.
Saute beef and onions together until browned.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, add rice and seasoning over 1/2 the zucchini.
Cover with beef mixture and spoon over the cottage cheese.
Add remaining zucchini, then spread soup over all.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbling. Serves 8.

title: lavosh
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add sesame seed.
Cut margarine into flour; add milk.
Shape dough into small round balls.
Roll out thin, using lots of flour with rolling pin.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 8 to 12 minutes.
Brush off excess flour after cooling.

title: pastel wine cake
directions: Beat for 3 minutes all ingredients on medium speed.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over cooled cake.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs and melted butter. Press into pan.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Spread on crust.
Mix the Cool Whip, 1 cup cold milk and vanilla together.
Spread on cream cheese.
Let set about 5 minutes.
Spread pie filling on top.
Chill and serve.

title: cherry date holiday bars
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cherries.
Place in buttered pan; bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir well.
Cool until you can handle. Shape into balls around cherries and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces in butter. Set remaining butter aside.
Roll in crumbs.
Place in shallow casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
To leftover butter, add remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked chicken.
Bake 20 minutes more or until done.
Serves 4.

title: curried fruit compote(armenia)
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix butter, brown sugar and curry powder. Dot over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and refrigerate for at least one day.
Warm over at 350° for 1/2 hour until bubbly.

title: herb chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix cut up chicken, soups, chow mein noodles and evaporated milk.

Place all of this mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 smaller casserole dishes. Saute the onion and celery in margarine until onion and celery are soft. Combine this with seasoned stuffing mix and spread over the top of the chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Blend tomato soup and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Makes 2 1/2 cups dressing.

title: pear lime mold
directions: Add enough water to syrup to measure 1 cup.
Bring to a boil. Stir into gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mash pears, beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Add to gelatin.
Mix well.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped cream.
Chill until set.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Combine everything, except oil, in blender pitcher.
Blend at medium speed until smooth.

title: short-cut baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In hot butter in small skillet, saute onions until tender, about 5 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole or bean pot, combine onion with rest of ingredients, except salt pork; mix well. Make cuts in salt pork every 1/2 inch.
Place in center of beans.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours; stir occasionally. Makes 8 servings.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Stir flour into corn; add slightly beaten egg.
Add the milk; dot with butter on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Remove skin and all visible fat from chicken. Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels. Combine honey and mustard in a small bowl and pour over chicken. Bake 25 minutes. Turn chicken and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, basting every 10 minutes, until meat is tender. Total preparation time is 10 minutes and cooking time is 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: hungarian pork paprika
directions: Cut boneless pork in strips.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Toss with meat.
Brown meat, garlic and onion in hot oil. Stir in tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 20 minutes or until meat is tender, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Take 1/2 cup of mixture from skillet.
Blend with sour cream, then add sour cream mixture back into remaining mixture in skillet.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles.
Very good with chicken or beef.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
If making in advance, add bananas just before serving.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and add beaten egg and flour and mix.
Drop by tablespoon in hot oil.
Cook in oil until golden brown on both sides.
Good with applesauce.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mash first 4 ingredients and mix together.
Mix together sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning mix.
Spread bean dip in shallow serving dish.
Top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream mixture; sprinkle with chopped onions, olives and tomatoes.
Cover with cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Put ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir well and let simmer for 4 to 8 hours.
May serve as soon as hot.
If you don't want to wait for the crock-pot, heat quickly on the stove and let simmer for a few minutes.

title: plains, georgia roasted peanuts(even elephants like them)
directions: Melt butter or oleo in microwave in glass baking dish.
Spread nuts in a single layer.
Mix to coat with butter.
Cook uncovered 8 minutes (Medium High 600W) or until golden brown.
Stir occasionally (so peanuts do not burn).
Spread nuts on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.
Stir to coat peanuts.
Cool and serve.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for loaves or 375° for muffins.
Beat eggs slightly and stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into well-greased pan or paper liners.
Bake loaves 50 minutes (makes 2).
Bake muffins 24 minutes (makes 24).

title: italian beef
directions: Place roast in roasting pan. Combine remaining ingredients, except pepper slices and hard rolls.
Pour over roast.
Roast in a 325° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven. Slice beef thinly and return to juices for 2 hours on low temperature.
Green pepper slices may be baked along with sliced beef in last oven stage. Serve on hard rolls along with juices.

title: no sugar applesauce raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is dissolved.
Add applesauce, eggs, oil, then remaining ingredients.
Mix well by hand.
Put in 8-inch square pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix soups and water together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in rice and spread out.
Layer chops on top.
Bake 1 hour covered at 350°.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Add bananas, milk and flour alternately.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar.
Let stand overnight to drain in colander over pan.
Discard liquid.
Mix marshmallows, walnuts, grapes and whipped cream.
Transfer ground cranberries into this and fold in.
Chill for 24 hours for best texture.

title: bacon cheese puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Add baking powder and bacon bits.
Place 6 crackers at a time in a circle on a paper plate.
Top each cracker with 1 teaspoon cheese mixture.
Heat on Medium 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute in 1 cup margarine until soft the onion, celery and pepper.
Add the frozen chopped broccoli and the mushroom soup. Cook the rice in 2 cups water with 1 teaspoon butter and the salt for about 15 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz to rice.
Mix all together with sauteed mixture.
Put into lightly buttered casserole; top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute on medium-high the onion, green pepper and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add crab, mushrooms, lemon juice, parsley and lemon pepper.
Add noodles and toss.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and let thaw and stir together.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom and spinach soup
directions: Heat vegetable oil in heavy large saucepan over medium-low heat. Add minced onion and garlic; saute until onion is tender, about 8 minutes.
Increase heat to high. Add all mushrooms and thyme and saute until mushrooms release their liquid, about 5 minutes. Add chicken stock and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bring to simmer before continuing.)
Add spinach and parsley to soup and stir until wilted. Season soup to taste with salt and pepper.
Ladle into bowls and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine liquid ingredients together.
Pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Mix batter only until moist.
Add cheese.
Drop into greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 muffins.

title: carol's no-fail cherry cobbler
directions: Heat 1 large can of cherries or any other type of fruit, juice and all.
Mix all ingredients.
Melt 1 stick of butter in a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour the mixed batter over the top of the melted butter, then pour hot fruit over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mock strawberry pie
directions: Mix boiling water and jello together and let cool.
Mix in strawberries and pour into a cooked pie crust.
Place in refrigerator to jell.
Top with cool-whip or whipped cream.

title: beef noodle
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add butter, garlic, salt, sugar, pepper and tomato sauce and simmer over low heat 15 to 20 minutes. Combine the onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Using a 2-quart casserole, alternate the layers of beef mixture, cream cheese mixture, cooked noodles and grated cheese and repeat.
Sprinkle top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Stir gently to coat.
Mix beaten eggs and melted butter together.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In a heavy pan (I use a Dutch oven) cook the small pieces of stew meat on a low heat, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and raise heat to brown.
Remove meat.
Add 1 cup water and bouillon. Simmer onion and chili powder.
Add tomatoes and Ranch Style beans. Stir meat back in and simmer 30 minutes or more.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Top with grated cheese.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil in salt water the chicken; cool and debone.
Set aside. Heat all chicken soup, milk, green chilies, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Set aside.
Layer in 2-quart casserole dish, lightly greased, large flour tortillas, chicken soup mixture and grated cheese.
Layer until all ingredients are used up.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour until cheese is melted and food is heated through.

title: individual chicken bake
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; divide equally into 6 (6 ounce) custard cups coated with cooking spray.
Cover loosely with foil; bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Uncover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove chicken from custard cups.
Top each serving with cranberry sauce.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 X 13 greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. While cake is baking make the frosting. Soften 1/2 stick margarine and 1-8 oz package of cream cheese to room temperature. Add 1 cup brown sugar and beat until smooth. Spread on cake while STILL HOT ! Sprinkle with nuts.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Peel and slice potatoes in casserole dish.
Top with ground beef and 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs with a rotary beater about 5 minutes until heavy peaks stay on beater when lifted.
Beat in sugar, a little at a time.
Gently mix in water and vanilla.
Gently mix in flour mixture.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield: 8 servings .

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food grinder.
Put in sugar.
Let dissolve.
Grind apples and oranges.
Stir into cranberries.
Melt Jell-O in 1 cup hot water, then 1 cup cold water.
Mix all together and let jell in icebox.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, smoked beef, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and chopped onion together with blender.
Shape into ball. Mix parsley and pecans.
Press onto cheese ball.
Refrigerate. (Best when made night before.)
Serve at room temperature with "party crackers".

title: sesame seed dips
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add milk and mix well.
Turn out on well-floured board and sprinkle with flour until desired consistency.
Knead about 10 times.
Roll out, making a rectangle. With a floured knife, cut in strips approximately 1/2 x 4 inches.

title: rose roggie chocolate cake
directions: Add hot water to chocolate.
Cream the butter. Add sugar, a little at a time, and cream thoroughly. Add sour milk, eggs and chocolate.
Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Bake in two 9-inch round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking dish or pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into melted butter.
Do not stir.
Add can of fruit and juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown. Crust will rise to top.

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Soften crust according to package directions; place in pie pan.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar vanilla and 1 egg; beat until smooth.
Set aside.
Reserve fudge packet from brownie mix for topping.
In large bowl, combine brownie mix, oil, 1 tbsp. water and remaining 2 eggs.
Beat 50 strokes with spoon.
Spread 1/2 cup brownie mixture in bottom of crust lined pie pan.
Spoon and carefully spread cream cheese mixture over brownie layer.
Top with remaining brownie mixture and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter as for making cake.
Add egg yolks and white and beat well.
Add water and vanilla and beat again.
Pour into a pie plate lined with pastry and bake until filling sets, about 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Fill large pot with water and season with salt, pepper, parsley and brown sugar.
Add the ingredients and cook for several hours.
Makes a large amount and it freezes well.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt, and pepper.
Moisten potatoes with water and roll in the mixture, coating them well.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for one hour.
Turn once during baking.
When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: judy weisgerber grandma's red cinnamon cucumber pickle rings
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into rings 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick; remove seeds.
Mix lime and water, add cucumber rings and soak 24 hours.
After cooking, rinse and drain. Cover with fresh water; let stand 3 hours and drain.

title: peanut butter cup bars
directions: Mix together and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 (12 ounce) bag chocolate chips, melted.
Chill.

title: roast beef perfection prime rib
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place roast on rack in shallow baking pan, rib side down.
Sprinkle with salts and pepper; place roast in oven and cook 1 hour.
Turn off.
Keep the oven door closed! Forty-five minutes before serving, turn the oven to 300°.

title: corn bake
directions: Drain whole corn.
Melt butter and add to sour cream in a bowl.
Add eggs, Jiffy mix and both corns.
Mix well.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: lazy man's stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake for 3 hours at 325°. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: super lemonade
directions: Slice oranges and lemons thinly.
Barely cover with water. Let stand an hour.
Take out pulp and discard rinds.
Dissolve acid in 1 cup warm water and add to the mixture along with the pineapple.
Dissolve sugar in enough water to make 3 gallons and add to the fruit mixture.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix Tang, milk and sour cream until smooth and orange in color.
Add half of the Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate until ready to eat.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Pour over chopped cabbage.
Mix tomato soup with 1 cup of water.
Pour over beef and cabbage.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a covered casserole dish.

title: party chicken
directions: Have "Carl" purchase an 80 to 100 pound hog, then have him cut it in half lengthwise.
To begin with, start 1 bag of charcoal in the large cooker grill, then add as needed.
A 100 pound pig takes about 7 hours to cook.
Flip the pig one time.
The first 3 1/2 hours, cook him belly side down.
Baste with sauce.
Use Loudell Pafford Sizemore's sauce, submitted by Larry Sizemore, found in this book.
Note:
Ingredients and directions are together on this recipe.

title: sugarless fruit salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle pudding and gelatin over mixture.
Mix well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: honey bun cake
directions: By hand, mix together first four ingredients.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar/cinnamon mix.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Twirl and swirl the batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chinese style fried rice
directions: Bring 1 cup of the water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in rice. Remove from heat; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook egg in margarine in a 10-inch skillet until set.
Ad onion and the rice and cook and stir over medium heat until rice and onion are lightly browned.
Combine remaining water and soy sauce.
Stir into rice.
Makes 3 cups or 4 servings.

title: butter cookies and jelly
directions: Mix flour and butter in a bowl with hands.
Add yolks and then sugar.
Mix again and roll into small balls.
Use finger for hole; add jelly.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on top rack and 5 minutes on bottom rack.

title: glorified rice("like dessert")
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
In saucepan, combine uncooked rice, water, pineapple syrup and salt.
Stir to moisten rice.
Bring quickly to boil; cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add pineapple and lemon juice; cool.
Stir in marshmallows and banana.
Fold in cream and cherries; chill.
Serves 8.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion. Sprinkle crackers on top.
Dot with melted butter or margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, cheese and oregano.
Spoon over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: smoked tuna
directions: Stir to make paste.
Serve with Wheat Thins or favorite cracker as appetizer.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Place chops in a baking dish.
Salt well.
Top each chop with a lemon slice and a thin onion slice; sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Pour one tablespoon catsup over each chop.
Cover and bake one hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally.

title: jazzed up ice cream
directions: Mix all together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 275° oven.
Stir through 2 or 3 times while baking.
Be careful not to burn or scorch.
Remove and let cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and cook eggs, sugar and lemon juice mixture until thick, stir constantly to keep from burning and sticking to pan.
Remove from stove, put in refrigerator and let chill.
Then add to fruit the marshmallows and nuts.
Beat Dream Whip and add to this mixture. Pour into a dish and let set.
Chill.

title: diet shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whirl at high speed until frothy and blended.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a large pot of hot water, boil together the carrots, potatoes and celery for 10 minutes; drain and add beef, chicken and chicken broth.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cut tortillas in strips.
Cook corn tortillas in Crisco oil until crispy.
Dab with paper towel and remove grease.
Top each serving with Mozzarella, tomato and tortillas.

title: quick and easy pork
directions: Place pork chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chop onion and bell pepper and place on pork chops.
Mix can of mushroom and can of chicken soup together; pour over pork chops.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Combine tomatoes, tomato paste, onions and green pepper in saucepan. Simmer 30 minutes.
Empty tomato mixture into food processor or blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Return to saucepan. Add other ingredients. Bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Yields about 5 cups.

title: superb crab spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sausage rolls
directions: When margarine is frozen, grate into flour. Mix with enough water to hold together. Roll out a small piece of dough. Put sausage inside and roll up. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn temperature down to 375° and bake for 15 minutes. Makes estimated 3 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add butter, flour, sugar and salt, mix well. Stir in milk and corn.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted near center come out clean. Yield: 6 servings.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out into small balls.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: spiced oat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
In mixing bowl with electric mixer at high, beat butter and brown sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute.
Stir in squash.
Gradually stir in flour mixture, oats and raisins until combined.
Drop dough by 1/4 cupfuls onto baking sheets.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until lightly golden.
Remove to wire racks.
Cool for 1 hour.
Repeat with the remaining dough. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: ever crisp pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and cover with lime and water.
Let stand 24 hours, then rinse in cold water.
Let soak 3 hours longer in water, drain off water and cover with a mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Leave overnight and in the morning, put on stove. Boil for 35 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: orange and pineapple sherbet punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, ginger ale and gelatin, mixing well. Add both sherbets to drink mixture and serve.
Yields 20 to 25 (6 ounce) glasses of punch.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; let set overnight.
Mix marshmallows and pineapple in separate bowl.
Next day, mix all together and fold in Cool Whip.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in Bundt pan for 55 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan, spread pecans and coconut.
Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese and pour over unbaked cake and spread.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms and remove caps.

Saute whole caps in oil. Chop mushroom stems. Cook spinach according to package directions along with chopped mushrooms. Drain and squeeze to eliminate excess water. Combine with egg whites and bread crumbs. Fill mushroom caps with spinach mixture.
Place caps in an oiled ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Use as garnish around roast meat or chicken. Also may be served as an appetizer.

title: squash souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and butter in pan; boil until soft ball stage. Put chocolate chips and marshmallow cream together in pan, then pour other mixture over it.
Mix it.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Place in pan; cut in squares or drop onto wax paper.

title: ham deluxe
directions: In square, greased dish, arrange stuffing.
Top with broccoli, then cheese, then ham, then eggs.
Pour white sauce over this and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for one-half hour.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt the chocolate in the boiling water and let cool. Cream the butter and sugar until light. Add the egg yolks one at a time, beating after each. Add the vanilla and chocolate. Mix until blended. Sift together the flour, baking soda, and salt. Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture, alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Fold in the egg whites. Pour into three greased and floured round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dressing hot dish
directions: Spread ground beef into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chopped onion, celery and Stove Top with combined melted oleo and water. Spread over hamburger layer.
Next spread the chicken soup and celery soup over the dressing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.
In small mixing bowl mix tomato sauce, chili powder, onion and sugar and set aside.

title: pie crust
directions: Stir with a fork and roll between wax paper.
Makes one 9-inch crust.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Dissolve salt in the 2 quarts of water in enameled or stainless steel pan.
Add squash and onions and soak 12 to 18 hours.
Drain for an hour but do not wash or rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients in a kettle or pan and boil for 5 minutes. Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: amish cookies
directions: Combine margarine and sugars.
Beat 2 eggs into oil.
Add to sugar mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Mash crisscross with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: basic fluffy pancakes
directions: For Variation for Buttermilk Pancakes:
Use buttermilk in place of sweet milk and 1 teaspoon of baking soda instead of baking powder.

title: ragu spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onions, garlic and peppers in oil for 1/2 hour.
Put through blender until liquified.
Wash and core tomatoes; put into blender until liquified.
Boil everything together to desired consistency.
Add one large can tomato paste for added flavor and body.
Mix well.
Put in hot sterile jars.
Also freezes well.
Use as you would any commercial sauce.
Makes 30 pints.

title: ham salad filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread between buttered bread slices.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: steak stroganoff
directions: Remove fat from meat and brown.
Cut into bite size pieces. Add mushrooms and gravy.
Cook noodles and drain.
Serve steak and gravy over noodles.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Beat until fluffy. Gradually add Eagle Brand milk while stirring. Stir until thoroughly mixed. Add lemon juice and vanilla. Stir until well mixed. Turn into prepared crust. Chill 2 or 3 hours (do not freeze) before garnishing top of pie with cherry pie filling or cherry glaze.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined dry ingredients and mix well.
Press half crumb mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Spread with preserves. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: frozen pumpkin squares
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and press firmly on bottom of an 8-inch square dish. Chill 15 minutes.
Combine the milk, pumpkin, pumpkin pie spice and pudding.
Blend with electric mixer on low speed for 2 minutes. Fold in the whipped topping. Spoon over crumb crust in dish. Freeze for 4 hours.
When ready to serve, let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes. Cut into squares.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped cream and sprinkle of nuts.
Store any leftover dessert in freezer.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; cream until smooth.
Add powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook ingredients, except coconut, until thick.
Add coconut and pour into 8-inch baked pie shell.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Beat
egg and
sugar.
Melt
shortening
and
chocolate together.
Add
vanilla,
nuts and raisins, then add flour and milk alternately to make batter.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 420° oven for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Heat water, butter, sugar and salt to boiling in saucepan over medium heat.
Whisk in cornmeal and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and place in large bowl.
Whisk in milk until smooth. Add eggs and baking powder.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: gumbo
directions: Saute onions, garlic, bell pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Using stock from chicken, add chicken, okra and sausage pieces.
Bring to a gentle boil.
Add sauteed ingredients.
Add bay leaf and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	according
to directions on box; drain. Mix broccoli
with
cooked
rice.
Put	in large baking dish. Sprinkle onion
over mixture.
In a saucepan, heat Cheez Whiz and soup together.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Cook in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm or hot.

title: hamburger pepperoni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add Ragu sauce. Add water to thin this.
Cook rigatoni noodles as directed on package.
In a large casserole dish that has been well-greased, add in layers the noodles, hamburger mixture, sliced cheese and pepperoni.
Will make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice.
Add raisins, nuts, apples and orange rind.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Press in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled baked crust.
Mix milk and 2 packages instant pudding; beat for 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining chopped nuts.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add pineapple. Stir in bread cubes.
Bake in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, until lightly brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Great with ham!

title: easy cocktail wieners
directions: Cut wieners into bite size pieces.
Add wieners and barbecue sauce.
Simmer.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients; stir into gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Yields 20 servings.

title: raisin hermits
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and then soda dissolved in hot water.
Sift flour, measure and sift again.
(Reserve a little of the flour, you may not need it all.) Add cinnamon, raisins and nuts to flour and combine mixtures. Drop and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Try one cookie first and add more flour if necessary.

title: apricot-mustard grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Season tenderloin with salt and pepper. In small bowl, stir together the preserves and mustard. Grill pork over a medium-hot fire, brushing with mustard mixture frequently, turning once or twice, until just done, about 15 minutes.

title: brownies low calorie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in a bowl and stir until blended.
Put in greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: stick to ribs fruity oatmeal(dietetic)
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add oatmeal and salt.
Stir and cook 1 minute.
Stir in pineapple, cottage cheese and flavoring.
Bring to a boil.
Serve with sweetener and milk as meal plan permits. Yield: 1 serving.

title: carrot salad
directions: Layer vegetables in dish (with a cover).
Combine soup, vinegar, and oil and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate over night.

title: gazpacho
directions: Finely chop all vegetables.
(A food processor is ideal for this.)
Combine with all remaining ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.
Serve this soup chilled with one can of the following assortment of garnishes: finely chopped green onions, chives or croutons.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Boil chicken and use chicken broth to make the rice.
Debone chicken and cut into chunks. In large skillet or wok, mix all ingredients cook until hot, stirring often.

title: quick broccoli soup(makes 4 cups)
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until heated.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Spread evenly onto tortillas and roll up.
Wrap and chill before slicing and serving with picante sauce.

title: walnut party balls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in egg yolk. Sift flour into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and cherries.
Shape into small balls.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Dip balls in egg white, let drain then roll in chopped nuts.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake in hot oven at 400 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: creamy ham casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter; stir in flour and add milk all at once.
Cook until thickens, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and sour cream to sauce and stir until cheese melts.
Combine with cauliflower, ham and mushrooms.
Put in 2-quart casserole. Combine remaining butter (melted) with bread crumbs and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes or until hot.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Boil water, peanut butter, oleo or butter and salt.
Pour over mixture flour, sugar, baking soda, vanilla, eggs and buttermilk or milk with vinegar or lemon juice added.
Mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: honey mustard chicken wings
directions: Place chicken on cookie sheet in one layer.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, turning once.
Combine rest of the ingredients and toss with chicken wings.
Serve hot or cold.

title: light fettuccine alfredo
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour into small saucepan; cook sauce over very low heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Mix thoroughly with cooked fettuccine noodles.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef in pan with oil.
Add garlic and onion. Saute until meat loses its pinkness.
Drain off fat, if any.
Add cabbage, carrots, salt, peppercorn, bay leaf, broth and water. Heat to simmer.
Cook until cabbage is tender, about 10 minutes. Add peppers and soy sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: avocado dip
directions: Put on flat serving tray. First refried beans, then mix sour cream, avocado and taco seasoning and put that on the beans. Then top in order: chopped lettuce, onion, tomato, grated cheese, and sliced black olives. Serve with your favorite chips.

title: spiced beets
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add liquid.
Add to boiling beets.
Cook until thickened.
